name: Michael Kernan
text: Tried to visit for a date dessert with my wife but was ignored by the single employee working at 5pm. She was on the phone but made no attempt to even acknowledge us in the 10 minutes we waited. An owner or manager contact my wife via direct message after her Facebook review. I appreciate any attempts to make bad experiences right, but blaming the experience on it being a college town is not the right approach. You can hire people that are not students, there are plenty desperate for a job. You can train and follow up on training your employees, they are a reflection of you. If the simple answer is to blame your bad pool of employees, you are only making yourself look incompetent - you hired them! If your easy answer is to blame unmotivated college kids as your staff, why would I want your free cookies as recompense - made by unmotivated college kids? If you are excusing their awful customer service, why would I expect the cookies to be of decent quality? The products are extremely expensive yet you can't afford to have 2 employees during peak times? Must not being doing that well. Shame to see another business waste their short time in Tuscaloosa by not trying. Bye bye Whimsy!

resp.text: I hate you had a bad experience. I love my employees like family but mistakes happen and I hate that what I responded made it seem like I blame them because my front sakes staff are college students. That was my mistake. I take full responsibility. My back staff that make my product have many years of experience between them and I also help out when needed. We hope to keep growing as a business and learn from our mistakes. We want to continue to serve the community and hope that the community continues to support us. I hope we can all learn from your bad experience.

Came in to buy cookies and the employee was on the phone with a customer - understandable. We were never acknowledged or even looked at for that matter for the nearly 10 minutes we waited on her to complete a $30 sale over the phone. Poor excuse of a business and I expect Whimsy to close quickly with this poor excuse of customer service.

Edit: the business has since messaged me blaming the college students for the poor service and offered cookies. College students are not an excuse for poor service - don't move to a college town when you're going to throw them under the bus. Poor excuse. Remember that they chose to hire these people and chose to save the money on labor to not staff more people in the store.

We ended up going to Nothing Bundt Cakes not too far from here and received the most incredible service and a superior product. I really recommend them if you're in Tuscaloosa or Hoover!

text:
Not impressed. They were out of several flavors, had only a few cupcakes of the remaining flavors, although they did have an extra flavor in the back that was not in display. The cupcakes themselves were smaller than others I have seen in different bakeries, but that wasn't so much an issue for us as the taste. AWFUL! I didn't even finish the chocolate one. The caramel one with the graham cracker bottom was ok but nothing great. My husband said my cupcakes from home were better .... and so were the kind from a box mix. Especially at the cost - more than $6 for two cupcakes.
We won't be going back.

name: Latanya Stamps
text: They were okay for my first time getting one. They r alot smaller then other places i have been n montgomery that also sell cupcakes. Redvelvet cake has its own unique tast and i didnt get that.

name: Anthony Brown
text: Good Bakery....

name: EliJah Duck
text: I definitely recommend this place I had extremely fast service. I ordered a large cinnamon bun and four minis for my kids. The blueberry lemonade was out of this world. I definitely recommend that as well. The guy that took our order was extremely friendly. I give it a A++

name: Leatha Watson
text: My favorite The Cinnabon with the sprinkles nut with caramel. yummy!!

text: The worst Cinnabon I’ve ever had. The Cinnabon was thin as paper. Definitely will not be returning!

text: they’re lucky they get one star. Just left and paid for two frozen drinks and only received one so after 10 minutes of waiting I go back up there and tell the guy I had another drink and without making eye contact he says “I’m makin it for you” so I sit back down WAITING and 15 mins later still no drink so I got aggravated I left. Worst experience ever it was on my receipt I paid for it I believe they should’ve made more communication.

text: First the smell then mmm the taste priceless.

text: Best Cinnabon staff and experience I’ve had yet! Everyone is so friendly there and they remember regular guests by name or face a lot and take great care of their fellow mall employees.

text: We've been very pleased, each time we visit. I'm sure you'll enjoy all the treats they have.

name: Tiffany Lewis
text: No drive thru?...Would love to have a Cinnabon building with a drive thru.

name: mysterkeelhaul SJMS
text: Great food and wonderful people. Just as good as the Five Loaves location downtown.

name: Christi Day
text: Absolutely delicious food, fantastic service and cute atmosphere, definitely recommend!!!

name: Denise Brasher
text: $80 cake but Publix is better!  I ordered a 10" cake for a special event at my daughters school.  I saw that a 8" was $35-$45 so I went ahead and ordered a 10" thinking okay this may be around $50 or so.  I went to pick it up and it was over $80 - WHAT!!!  So I wasn't giving a $80 cake away. We went to Publix and gave that cake away. So we decided for $80 this had better be the best cake of our lives. We invited family over for dinner and we all dug in.  Well the chocolate cake was moist but the Salted caramel and the icing was not good.  NO ONE finished their slice.  For $80 we should've cleaned our plates and been asking for seconds.  My MIL didn't even want to take the extra home.  So disappointed.  My wedding cake didn't even work out to cost that much.  I would not recommend buying from here.  Someone had mentioned Edgar's to me but I thought they said Edward's - I'll be going there from now on.

name: Christy Holden
text: Delicious every time! I love to pop in and grab a quick meal and a slice of cake. Fast and friendly staff!

resp.text: Christy, I'm grateful to know you're such a fan of our cakes, meals, and speedy service! The team looks forward to having you here. -Cynthia Bertolone, Owner

name: Birmingham South Campground
text: When our co-workers have birthdays we always celebrate with take out for lunch.We tried Cake Art for the first time today and absolutely loved our experience! The man who took our phone order was very precise. The meal was ready in a timely manner and ALL of our orders were correct. It was delicious and we will be ordering from these folks often!

name: Jessa Garrett
text: Cake Art By Cynthia Bertolone did both the cake and the catering for my wedding, and everyone was thrilled! From the gorgeous cake to the delicious pork tenderloin and chicken piccata, the guests could not stop talking about the wonderful options. Cynthia and her team created a custom menu for us and they were there throughout the entire process. They set up and cleaned up, so there was no stress the day of for me! Thank you so much Cake Art!!

resp.text: Jessa, it was such a blast working with you to create the perfect menu for your wedding. I'm so happy you and your guests all loved the cake, pork tenderloin, and chicken piccata. Thanks for making our bakery a part of your special occasion. I hope to work with you for another celebration again soon! -Cynthia Bertolone, Owner

name: Lambo Moto
text: The food is awesome and everyone is super friendly! Give it a try you won’t be dissapointed.

resp.text: So glad our food and service didn't disappoint, Tyler! We'd be happy to welcome you back here soon. -Cynthia Bertolone, Owner

name: Connie Settles
text: The food here is delicious. Mrs. Cynthia was very accommodating to the food allergies my family has and the service was personal, warm and friendly. We had the lasagna, spinach calzone, spaghetti and meatballs and the chicken salad. Everything was delightful. The strawberry cake is a must have if you are in the area...do yourself a favor and get some CAKE. Some of the best cake I have had...not to sweet, light and fluffy....fresh strawberries....mmmmm!

resp.text: It' was our pleasure to customize and personalize your meals to meet all of your tastes and dietary needs, Connie. From the first bite of spinach calzone to the last bite of strawberry cake, it seems like your meal was a hit! Hope you'll be back for more summery sweetness soon! -Cynthia Bertolone, Owner

name: mike foreman
text: Food is wonderful. We were very happy with everything we ordered.

resp.text: I'm happy to hear that you were pleased with your experience, Mike! Thanks for the review, and we'll see you next time. - Cynthia Bertolone, Owner

name: Gretchen Evans
text: I discovered this little gem about 2 months ago via a Facebook picture. I ordered my daughters Bday cake and it was phenomenal. No leftovers. Everyone raved, I have since been back for take out lunch, cake slices, pastries, and cupcakes. I seriously can't find anything I don't like. Try it, it will NOT disappoint

name: Christopher Jahraus
text: This is a fantastic place, run by the family of the original Joe's Italian Restaurant in Alabaster.  They put so much passion into what they do, it can't help but result in phenomenal food and cakes beyond belief!

resp.text: Christopher, it is wonderful to hear that our passion and the love for our bakery has come across to you. We can't imagine doing anything else! Thank you for all of the support. We'll see you soon! -Cynthia Bertolone, Owner

name: Sunny kang
text: I love your carrot cake make more

resp.text: Thanks for the support, Sunny! We're thrilled you're a fan of the carrot cake. Hope you'll make it back our way again soon. -Cynthia Bertolone, Owner

text: picked up lunch today for coworker and I , HUGE portions , homemade authentic Italian food - Fast and friendly service . We will most definitely be back for more - you've gotta see the cake slices to believe it!

resp.text: Glad you enjoyed stopping by, Trent! Come see us again soon. -Cynthia Bertolone, Owner

text: I love the mocha latte I got here! Also it’s a “mom & pop” coffee shop and it has a comfortable, pleasant atmosphere. To be honest I am thankful to have an alternative to *St———*! 💪🏼

resp.text: Happy to have another satisfied 5 Star customer! Thank you and we look forward to seeing you often! Blessings ~ Sandy & Trish

text: The coffee is fantastic, but the kind and thoughtful service is even better! Southern hospitality is abundant :)

resp.text: Thank you so much!

name: Roxan Pagasian
text: Small and cozy place with efficient service. The food was excellent. Both bagels were top of our visit!

name: Bill McCown
text: I visited Toomer's Coffee for the first time last week.  It was truly an enjoyable experience.  My "to go" cup was perfect - bold but balanced.  The bag of whole bean coffee that I purchase was very high quality.  Additionally, I enjoyed the visit with the owners.

resp.text: Thanks!

name: Julie Nelson
text: Loved the coffee, and the cookies are to die for! I'll be back

resp.text: Thanks Julie! Look forward to your next visit!

name: Skulls Williams
text: My wife stops in from time to time and brings me coffee to work. They sell an amazing product. I got their keto coffee this morning and it was made perfectly.

resp.text: Thanks! We make them the same way we drink them. Cheers.

name: Brad Donnelly
text:
Really smooth delicious one of a kind taste! Truly excellent roasting and custom techniques used to attain excellent coffee. Coffee beans come from Ethiopia and other Rain Forrest countries to give you the very best bean to be brewed into a little cup of heaven!

I know I have watched Sandy in their little roasting shop in Opelika and have seen first hand the roasting expertise that Sandy uses in customizing these wonderful coffee blends.

I love the Auburn City Blend it is wonderful!  If you have not tried Toomer's Coffees you are missing out on a real one of kind custom blended coffee!  Treat yourself to a couple of pounds of each of their blends you will never go back to another coffee brand.

resp.text: Go Brad! Thanks!

name: Pollyanna Brannan
text:
First time I had their coffee I knew it was different and in a GREAT WAY!! I met the owners and have to assume that their time spent living in South America is where they learned good coffee and why it's important to use direct trade coffee beans - truly ethically sourced coffee beans
I love that it is family owned and made in Alabama because I think it is important to buy local when you can and the product is quality. I even quizzes them to find out details that are important and found that they make sure it is low acid, infrared roasted!!!!!  That to me is great customer service putting the special effort into "doing it right!!!" Having fast inexpensive shipping is a bonus!!! <wink> but all of this makes me love the brand. Had to share!! How often does some one slow down to share a positive?! Not enough so I wanted to make sure I shared this one because they earned it!

resp.text: Thanks Pollyanna!

name: Viann Whitten
text: Toomer's Coffee Roasters is awesome! Mr. and Mrs. Toomer lived in South America so they know coffee. Many people have given up drinking coffee due to stomach sensitivity but you don't have to anymore! Toomer's Coffee Roasters uses an Infrared coffee roaster so no more bitter taste and no high acid, just smooth wonderful coffee. Toomer's Coffee Roasters has cheap fast shipping too. Love this company. Best kept secret in Auburn, Alabama.

resp.text: Thanks Vivian

name: Logan Moore
text: Toomers Coffee is phenomenal! The best coffee in Alabama let alone Auburn /Opelika area! Sandy and Trish have been around the world to hone their craft and have brought a world class roastery to Opelika! If you are in town for ballgames or shopping their new store front is very close to tiger town and totally worth the stop in! Best brewed coffee ever! Auburn City Blend, Snickerdoodle, Vermont Maple But...everything they do is great!

resp.text: Thank you! You're very kind.

name: JOE LEOS
text: I had the joy of speaking with the owner Toomer's Coffee about the different coffees and their tastes. I bought the following coffees Auburn City Blend, Colombian Supremo and Ethiopian Yigacheffe Aricha Gedio. The coffees were all wonderful in taste and aroma but our favorite is Auburn City Blend.  Please take time to drop by and pick up some of the best local coffees Toomer's Coffee has to offer.

resp.text: Thank you Joe for your affirming words! It's a pleasure to do what we do and serve those like you. Blessings.

name: Dan McNiff
text: Great coffee and great people.  We have been looking for a strong local roaster, I believe we just found them!

resp.text: Thanks Dan! Enjoyed meeting you guys!

text: These ladies make some amazing cakes. They look beautiful, but they taste even better. The icing is so light and fluffy, and the cake itself is so moist and delicious having been soaked in milk. The whole experience is delightful. They also have candles and cake accessories in the store, which is very helpful. I also had a few of the fruit-filled empanadas from the display on the counter, which were pretty tasty. If you're ever near Chandalar in Pelham, you've got to check them out!

name: Matt Taylor
text:
Cakes are good, but not sure they are worth the price. It would have been nice to try some of the many flavors, especially after reading so many other reviews from people talking about being able to taste before they buy. It also would be nice to see the cakes, but all you see are boxes and shirts.

We were told there was only one size available, small.

And can someone please explain why there is a tip jar, or why I'm expected to leave a tip to someone who has placed a bagged cake in a box, tapes it closed, and hands it to me when there is really nothing special/personable they did compared to any other place, there are NO samples, and the cakes are so expensive in the first place?

resp.text:
Matt,

I am sorry to just be responding to you, as I am just seeing this review. We are sorry your first experience at Rum Sisters was not the best. You must have been here right around Christmas. All the boxes you are referring to were some of the thousands of shipments we had going out for the holidays. It does not surprise me that we ran our of samples at that time of year, as we were running out of cake, too. We didn't even have cakes for display. That also explains why we only had our medium sized cakes available, what we call a small (feeds 6-8). Normally we do have samples available and all cake sizes in every flavor, as well. It was just an off day for us.

Regarding the tip jar at the counter; our staff are trained in every aspect of the bakery- each person bakes cakes, wraps the cakes, boxes the cakes, washes the dishes/pans and handles many other incidentals in addition to offering customer service at the counter. As to whether you felt the service warranted a tip or not, is completely up to you. As the owner, I think it's nice to offer the option if someone feels they have received excellent service, as my staff work very hard.

The prices of our cakes reflect the quality ingredients we use and the labor intensive process involved in making the cakes. We offer cake from $5 to $45. based on servings that's about $2.25 for a slice of alcohol infused cake. I would also like to point out that alcohol is very expensive in the state of Alabama. So, if you are comparing regular cake pricing to alcohol infused cake pricing- they are just not the same.

We would like to have you back and try all the cakes! Please, give us another try. We strive for excellence and hope you can see that the next time you are in.
Thank you for your review and we hope to see you again, soon.

text:
The idea of making rum cakes is awesome.  That's why I was excited to go there to try some rum infused creations. When I entered the store, I was hoping to see multiple choices of cakes on the displays, but instead I saw sheleves full of folded T-shirts with their logo, I believe. For a moment I  thought I got into wrong store, because there were no cakes whatsoever. All of them were behind cash  register, they looked identical, wrapped and too far away from the customer.
To be honest, I was disappointed. I've decided to taste several flavors to decide which one I like the best. I couldn't taste rum flavor at all and consistency of each of them was too buttery, even detected margarine flavor. That's not what I expected in rum infused cakes. Unfortunately, that was good idea to create these cakes, but not very successful execution. As a business owner, instead of Tshirts I would put cake samples on the display. This is cake shop after all.

name: Barrett Lee
text:
I discovered these guys a few years ago at the Gulf Shores annual shrimp festival and OMG it was one of the very best cake I have ever tasted, seriously great flavors and infused with some sweet tasting rum. I was thrilled to find out that their shop was just a couple miles up the road. I was also happy that  I wasn't getting hooked on this newly discovered favorite  only to start my usual long distance shopping and shipping relationship. Whew!

I fid have one huge scare when I pulled in the parking lot one day, to get myself a cake or two :-) and my heart sank, oh no they're gone!! Bur I noticed a little paper on the door with a notice, they had moved and only over to Orange Beach, emergency avoided. I rushed over to the new place, which by the way is in a large outdoor mall with tons of parking on Beach Blvd. and the new dogs has a spacious and perfectly climate controlled interior with cushy swivel bar chairs. You can sit at the bar/counter and choose which one of the 8 or so flavors of rum cake you would like to sample. Isn't that fancy? Oh and you can get a coffee or milk or something whilevyou're at it, oh oh oh what's that ICE CREAM? Hey I didn't know what was going on because my favorite rum cake place was just this cramped, not too well lit, and usually a little too warm hole in the wall and not this Rodeo Dr boutiquey place where the pries were certainly going to get jacked up.

Wait, no need to panic as I see the cakes as just as good and the prices are the same and come to find out their old landlord took half if their already cramped space away and they had no choice but to find a bigger place. Well thank you very much evil landlord because I don't mind driving a few more minutes for my favorite island guilty pleasure.

Indeed these rum cakes are absolutely delicious and they are really moist, full of infused flavor and their cakes actually melt in my mouth, seriously.

I used to pretend that I just couldn't decide on which flavor I wanted in a full cake and therefore I would just have to take the 6 smaller (1 or 2 person size) or the sampler package. I would say that I needed to spend more time making up my mind, nope no more pretending,  now I just walk in and buy  my six favorite flavor cakes (iall the flavors are my favorites) and I'm getting my deal of 6 for the price of 5, well okay everybody gets that deal. These scrumptious little cakes are bigger than a fat cupcake and way better and besides now I'm getting my rum cakes in a six pack for the weekend and the big game or to go with the cookout. ;-)

I'm not sure if the ladies that I originally met at the festival are actually sisters but take it from a real sailor, from way back, that's actually seriously high caliber and delicious rum. Whether it's dark rum or cocunut or some other flavor the sisters seem to masterfully pair the perfect cake recipe with the perfect premium rum. Speaking of sisters one of my many favorites is called "twisted sista" and I will say, while I write this and my mouth begins to water, that I have never settled on just one favorite. But hey that's okay because "Big O" will forever be my  first and my latest crush is "Bushwacker" Ooooo it's so good!

I was super psyched when I discovered that they started making these slices of goodness available for ordering and shipping through
Amazon because my six packs make a great gift and I have already shipped out some of these for birthday and Christmas gifts to some of my truly favorite friends and even a few relatives. Whether you buy them in-person or online they're still hand made, labeled and have little bows on them from these local folks and by the way you can get small, medium and large sizes for any size occasion. They are truly delicious cakes and now you can also get cookies and ice cream when you go in for your cake fix I think I'll have to go today :-)

Ahoy!! Ho ho ho and a six pack of rum cakes!!

text: We went on a Saturday morning about an hour after open. The space and concept are really cool and something that Huntsville has not previously had. Ordinarily, this wouldn’t be a big deal- because we planned to just drink our coffee until they came out. But they will not let you pre-order any food. So if you reach the counter when they’re sold out, you have to go to the end of the line again and hope they have something left by the time you’re up. Ultimately, they may figure this out and be ready for prime time soon (the line was well out the door), but we left hungry and disappointed. We will give them another try in several months when they have hopefully straightened out their logistics.

text: Stopped here after seeing their Pizza sign.  I expected something bland and regular like every other place that tries pizza, but this was the best pizza I've ate.  Think crust. It took us 12 minutes to get our pizza, which is nothing - we typically spend more time than that in a drive in waiting,  but wife and I enjoyed a nice chat with the owner while pizza was cooking.  While eating, it seemed like 20 customer came in to either pick up, order, or get something on the go.  Owner waited on everyone of them, knowing half of them by name when they walked through the door.  Great little gem in the town of Hartselle.  We will be back.

text: Love this place.  We've been coming here for quite a while.  This place is crazy busy on weekends and holidays, but they are always super friendly and helpful. name: Belsogi Adrian
text: My father attended a government meeting in Huntsville several weeks back.  The man leading the project brought a strawberry, chocolate, and vanilla cake from his wife's bakery.  This wasn't 3 cakes, it was all in one.  He has talked about this cake for weeks.  He doesn't even typically eat sugar, so I knew it had to be good.  He couldn't remember the name of the bakery until we googled neapolitan cake in Alabama.  Then BAM.  He instantly recognized it was a Molly Moo Cake.  I was hoping to order one for Thanksgiving, but turns out it is 14 hrs away.  He says he's bringing us a whole one home to Virginia when he heads back to Huntsville in January.  I can't wait to try it.

name: Rebecca Layague
text: They made the cake for my wedding shower and it stole the show! Covered in beautiful delicate rosettes it was veeery bridal and the frosting wasn't overpowering like you might expect it would be. I was so greatful to my girlfriends for getting me this cake because it had that look of being very elegant and formal plus the taste matched! Five stars all the way.

name: Teresa Smith
text:
This rating is based SOLELY on the appearance of the cake I ordered - not the taste or texture - those things couldn't be beat.  The cake tasted amazing, and that part would get a solid five stars. However, what I ordered/expected...and what I was handed when I went in to pick it up are two VERY different things.  (photos attached to the review)

I asked them to make a birthday cake using our car club's logo (photos attached). I've always been impressed with Ashley's decorating and never had a bad experience so I didn't give any further instructions other than saying I trust Ashley's design aesthetic.

I stopped by around 2:30 in the afternoon just to see if it might be ready (my pickup time was to be about 6:30) and there were two younger girls behind the window decorating cakes, I didn't see Ashley anywhere. (I did see a stunning Harry Potter themed three-tier cake in the window -  it was truly beautiful.) They said they'd call me when it was ready and it would probably be before the expected 6:30 pickup time. They never called, I went back at 6:15. I walked in and was truly taken aback by how bad this cake looked. I didn't know what to say....I had to excuse myself and go to the car for a second because I was about to cry. So embarrassed to take to this to an event after telling folks about how beautiful AND tasty their cakes are.

The issues were:
The colors are completely wrong (I think maybe they used leftover icing from another order instead of making the red and blue needed - it was burgundy and a sort of blue-gray color instead of true red and true blue). Ashley's comment about the color - well as it dries it'll be brighter. Nope. Didn't happen.

Then there are the circles - they aren't even circles. However, you can see the black lines on the cake that had been put there to trace in multiple places.

The letters are squished at the top and down the left side. They aren't sized nor shaped consistently across the whole cake for that matter.

Bottom line, I felt like I ordered a cake from a professional, and I got something that was decorated by an amateur. And honestly if Aunt Gussie had offered to make this for free and this is what I got - then ok. But that's not the case.

When I went back inside I told Ashley I wasn't happy, and that I thought it looked really bad. She did ask what I'd like her to do. I said I don't know what you can do since you close in 10 minutes and I have to be somewhere in 40 minutes and this cake has to go to Huntsville tonight. There's no time. So I paid and took the cake.

My advice, the cakes are delicious. But maybe don't order anything that needs to be free-hand drawn, because you may be severely disappointed. I rarely post reviews - but gosh i'd hate for someone to go pickup a cake for a big event and be as disappointed as I was.

name: Ali Staudt
text: Molly Moo’s did a cake for my wedding in February! It was absolutely the best cake I’ve ever had. Ashley is so easy to work with and the cake was exactly as I imagined it! Everyone was raving about how delicious it was and kept asking where it was from! There was not one bite left! She also did mini cupcakes to set around the cake and they were also delicious! If you are wanting a beautiful and delicious cake Molly moo’s is definitely the place to go! 5 star for sure!! Thank you guys!!!

text: I helped with a wedding  in which the bride's and groom's cake were both ordered from Molly Moo's. While both cakes tasted okay and looked okay (the grooms cake was quite a bit different than the picture they were given), they arrived 2 hours late. The bakery was 7 miles, approximately 13 minutes from the venue. The delivery time that was set up for 2 pm turned into 4 pm (and the wedding started at 5) therefore halting the decorating of both the bride and groom tables. There was no apology or explanation offered once the cakes finally arrived, nor on the phone when we called to inquire about the cakes, at which time whomever answered the phone wasn't polite at all. Obviously the cakes still had to be assembled and finished once they arrived, again 2 hours late, again interfering with other things that needed to be happening at this time, again without any sort of apology. Let me also mention that once the cakes were cut, approximately 2 hours after they arrived, which should have been 4 hours after they arrived, they were both still partially frozen inside. The lack of customer service, professionalism and dependability we experienced is enough for us to recommend you find someone else for your cake needs.

After reading the other reviews I have to say the staff here was very friendly the two times I went in.

text:
** HUBBY got out of Trouble w/ Tee's Cupcakes. **
My Hubby forgot what day it was. In a panic, he visited Tea's and they SAVE HIS HEINNEY with a fabulous Glamorous cupcake that was so AMAZING that I couldn't believe he found these. As I type this review, my co-worker (another husband panicking "What do I but my wife for her birthday".. he is looking at Tea's website and drooling. A great lil gem of a place. Thank you from David & Stephany Henson.

text: I love this place!  I do not go as often as I like because I cannot afford the weight gain it would cause.  Everyone that has helped me has been wonderful.  I think there is a "feel" here that you find when the people truly love what they do.  The selection may be smaller than other bakeries, but that is what I expect for a small, hometown bakery - quality over quantity.  Even then, I'm sure that if I requested anything in advance I could get it.

name: Art 2 Leo
text: Customer service💯...Oreo cake👌🏾...Peanut butter cake/cupcakes 🏁...and MUCH MORE. I was impressed upon arrival, witnessing one of the owners assist a customer to the car, with a beautifully decorated cake. GREAT PLACE.I’d give them 6 stars..

name: Joey Williams
text: Tried to order a Birthday cake for my daughter, was flat out told they could not get to it even with several days advance notice.  I have been faithful to this company since the first day they opened, but would not buy another thing from them, nor recommend them to anyone.

resp.text: Hello Joey thank you for your review. You just called about 30 minutes ago, if I'm not mistaken,  and asked the owner for a cake tomorrow(not advanced notice). We were more than happy to get you a traditional cake,  but you were wanting a custom designed cake.  I am completely booked on any custom cakes.  I try my absolute hardest to squeeze in as many last minute orders as I possibly can,  but I have a limit and there are people who order weeks and months in advance and I must honor their orders first.  I do apologize that we were not able to accommodate your request.

Cake was moist, fudge filling was awesome and the chocolate buttercream was not to sweet but had lots of flavor. Lots of other desserts and pastries to try here. She is waiting for the next occasion so we can order another cake. They were very good at getting this cake for me as it was on short notice a little over a day. Thank you!

You then sent a photo late Thursday evening via Facebook after  closing hours and needed the cake produced on saturday.  I simply told you no that I was booked. Won't spend my money or time here ever again. This is the new normal in America. His business must be one that is NOT struggling!!! Good Luck to you!!!

No you should respect that your rude behavior is costing you customers. It took everything in me not to respond like you. Sometimes a little kindness goes a long way instead you lost a customer because of your rude behavior.

resp.text: We are so sad to hear that you had a less than 5-star experience! Please contact our customer service team at customerservice@gfgmanagement.com and let us know what happened.

So after basically calling my son a liar my wife goes in and the same store manager lies and says she didn’t say this to my son and attempts to chastise my wife about how my son was wrong. Mind you, the employee that got the order wrong  just stands there and allows my son to take the blame for his mistake, he says nothing. Long story short, my wife wasn’t having it she threw the wrong order in the trash at the store, the store manager still had to give her the correct order and we will never purchase anything from there again.

How is this acceptable behavior?  This is my second time coming to this location and it has been HORRIBLE both times. Don’t waste your time here. You will be so mad after leaving that you won’t even taste the sub-par ice cream. Total time in store getting a cup of ice cream? 15 MINUTES. And no other customers were getting ice cream.

text: Our wedding happened in the middle of the COVID-19 pandemic, which ultimately meant going from a 200-person wedding to a 20-person wedding. The team was so accommodating and helped us reimagine a menu that ended up so delicious. I can’t tell you enough about how wonderful our barbecue, mac n’ cheese, potatoes and fruit tasted. On top of that, Stephanie took extra precautions to make sure everyone stayed safe and well fed. I highly recommend.

name: Alison Chatham
text: Prep for the wedding and everything was great. Ray was a great coordinator and really helped us out a ton when understanding what we need for our wedding. I unfortunately have to lower the rating because two specific members of the staff were incredibly rude to us, especially my husband on our wedding day. They forgot to bring out our champagne for all 150 of our guests for the toast. They didn't have any of the cake ready for the guests, we had to awkwardly stand there with no cake for the guests. After both of those occurrences, one of the rude staff members pulled my husband aside and yelled at him for having a terribly scheduled wedding, even though we gave the staff the schedule for weeks early, which we followed. The bartender was very kind, but there were several times where the bar was left unattended and I was having to wait there with a ton of guests to get a drink.  There even came a point where the drinks were left for guests to grab themselves, and some of our guests were taking whole wine bottles... which didnt seem compliant with ABC rules. They did clean up very nicely though, which was very kind since we had to clean up the venue ourselves afterwards.

The salad was ok (if you like zero nutrition iceberg lettuce) but I'm almost certain they used Kraft store bought dressing. Hello!!! This is someone's wedding reception. Do you have no respect for your work? The food was completely unacceptable. I pray that the parents of the bride got a full refund.

Talked to Ray gave him our totals. He told us his likes such as guess would appreciate tubs of bottle water iced down sitting around sounded good we bought bottle water. He said bottle beer was better less waste so we went that way. He is the professional.  Still no price was set.  Going to e mail it ?  Then he said bring your stuff down two days before anything you dont want to mess with. They really dont mean that. we showed up it was like they had never done it before. We should have set up night before staff was lost.  They were suppose to chill wine and beer all was hot. They had no ice for tea cokes drinks ??? Food was good not sure why they stopped serving before all was feed. We found bags of food in kitchen left. Then the food staff was gone. The bar staff was great trying to deal  food staff was slow but did ok. Left oven on  found that. oh did I mention There was no Ray or Bubba ?? And NO ICE BROUGHT! This is what 3000 got us.

name: J G (SouthernComfortLife)
text:
Let me tell you a true story, and how a 60th birthday party was ruined. My husband ordered a cake from Granna's Goodies for my birthday in good faith, and I sadly have to admit it was hands down the worst cake I have ever tasted or cut into. It was simply inedible. The texture was like rubber, the icing was grainy, and I couldn't serve it to my guests. Now, I'm all about supporting small business, and truly believe being honest with an owner is only fair so that they can make right by the issue at hand, and also to improve their product or service. I immediately called the owner and explained the issue with the cake. She was polite, sympathetic, and even offered to bake us another cake (hard pass) however, she never once offered to refund the money spent. I even physically took the inedible cake to her to show how awful it was, and all she said was 'sorry'.  I gave her ample opportunity to offer a refund (it shouldn't be my place to ask), and that is why I am writing this review.

As a previous small business owner myself of 30 years, it's Business 101 that you refund your customer if they have a viable complaint or dissatisfaction. No questions asked, no hassles. JUST DO IT. The cake I can do without and will never recommend Granna's for anything, but a 'sorry' isn't acceptable. I'm 'sorry' that I can't support a business that doesn't care about the quality of their products or doing the right thing by their customers.

You can tell they are new because they are still setting the place up.i went in for a coffee but noticed there were no tables and chairs set up.  Then I seen the cupcake case. These were beautiful. text: My wife has eaten at the best places in the world (literally) and is very finicky about her desserts.  She thought Louisa's were fantastic, esp. the croissants and the muffins.

name: Brad Seehawer
text:
Of Missy Mercer's trio of Cloverdale restaurants, Louisa's Bakery is the one most honest to who she is, offering a wide variety of uncomfortably large muffins and scones and normal-sized everything else, from biscuits to cheesecakes to sourdough to homemade granola. The imposing menu didn't quite represent the limited offerings in the display cases, but I get the feeling some of the bigger jobs are by request only.

Even just focussing on the muffins and scones, Louisa does a fine job. The giant muffins are loaded with whatever they're supposed to be, from mound of carrots to handfuls of chocolate chips that start smudging your fingers and lips as you attack it. The crumbly scones are great with a cup of coffee. The sausage and cheese biscuits are unique in that sausage and cheese is baked right into the bread, and while the crumbly sausage is cooked so far past the point of offering anything more than a hint of umami, I appreciate the creativity.

While the bakery is a worthwhile visit when you have a large order, you'll probably end up consuming most of your Louisa pastries at the adjacent Cafe Louisa, where you can enjoy her wares among good coffee and atmosphere.

name: Rose H.
text: Rickey J’s made the most adorable “baby shark” cake for my daughter’s birthday. The cake was absolutely beautiful and almost too pretty to eat. It was also the most delicious cake we’ve ever tried. This cake made my daughter’s birthday that much more special. I can’t say enough wonderful things about this amazing bakery. We will be using them for all of our special occasions.

resp.text: Thank you Mrs. Rose, we really enjoyed designing your cake. Look forward to serving you again.

text: I visited Rickey J's for the first time the other day. I purchased a few different flavors of the cupcakes. All I can say is...Awesome. Awesome cupcakes and most of all awesome service. I will be returning!

name: A Roper
text: This bakery is The Best in TOWN!!! I've visited this this bakery often. Mrs "J" is the sweetest person you will ever meet. The cinnamon rolls are THE BEST you will find. I have also have had several cakes made by her, and they have been DELICIOUS!! She has several types of cupcakes which are Very Good. You can't go wrong with anything from here. Lov It!!

resp.text: Thank you Mr. Roper,and we believe at Rickey J's that we have the Best Customers  in Town. We look forward to serving you again and again. Stay Blessed

name: Carmen Moore
text:
I ordered 2 dozen cookies, they were the best cookies I've ever eaten. The cookies were fresh, the flavor was excellent, the icing was a light glaze of perfection. Just the right amount of everything yummy. They were also very pretty. Wish I would have taken a picture but we ate all of them. The cake was pretty, fresh and delicious also.
5 stars for sure, plus one because the people are so nice!

resp.text: Thanks Carmen, so good to know you enjoyed everything. We look forward to serving you again. Stay Safe and GOD Bless !

name: Sandra Ward
text: The items were VERY reasonably priced even under-priced compared to other bakeries, and the man serving me was so very nice and hospitable!

resp.text: Thanks Sandra for the 5 star rating. Look forward to serving you again.

name: J Stamba
text: I see this baker at Grandview Hospital  selling slices of cake. Yet she only sells cupcakes in her store

resp.text: We apologize for the inconvenience, J Stamba. Our cake slices are an item specific to Grandview treat days. However, our cupcakes in the Bakery are just as delicious and are offered in the same flavors.

name: DANIEL campos
text: Wow! Great people! Great cakes! The frosting is a decadent texture and flavor! So happy I stopped buy and could support a local business! Good job!

resp.text: Hi Daniel, we thank GOD for the opportunity to serve wonderful people like you. Stay safe and blessed. See you soon. Thanks for 5 stars.

name: Mrs Batts
text: I was visiting my friend for her birthday and we drove past and decided on the way back we would stop in. Publix is where I Usually get my cakes, but was I in for a treat ordered the red velvet cake for her birthday and it was delicious. I just have one question do you all ship. My daughter prefers cupcakes, but said she wanted a cake from this bakery. If not we will make the 3.5 hour drive.

resp.text: Thanks Mrs. Batts, we're very happy that everyone enjoyed the cake. As of now we do not ship our cakes. Thanks again. God bless you and stay safe.

text: I love this gem! We've lived in the area for about a year & kept saying that we were going to check them out. I'm so glad that my husband & I finally stopped by. The owners are lovely... Ms. Janice (?) is just as sweet as her treats! Here's things you have to try: carrot muffins, brownies and cupcakes. They even have small sandwiches. I can't wait to try more items. Y'all have loyal customers with us!

We brought the cake home and my daughters’ reactions were absolutely priceless! Beautiful cake and was extremely yummy! We have found our forever bakery. ❤️

resp.text: Thanks  Kayla, so glad  we helped  to make the twins birthday  a big success. Welcome  to the neighborhood. Stay blessed.

I showed her and explained to her and she got it PERFECT!!! My guests loved it the taste and the look.and my birthday girl was thrilled. I also saw a few other cakes that people were picking up the days I went in there and they were also gorgeous! I highly recommend this place!

text:
One word...amazing!

My family and I  have used Rickey J.'s over the past 5 years for cupcakes, specialty cakes, sheet cakes, tiered cakes...just all of over the cake spectrum...and  have never been disappointed!

The cakes are beautiful AND delicious,  the prices are fair, and the customer service is exceptional!!

I highly recommend!!!

resp.text: Thank  you Shante', we are so happy  that you and your  family  enjoy  our cakes,  etc.It's  our pleasure  to serve you. God Bless

resp.text: Thanks  Grandview  Family. It's  always  a pleasure  to serve you. God bless  .

resp.text: Thank you Beth!

name: Erin Shockey
text:
I wish i could give Dreamcakes Cafe a million star review! Wow! I visited Dreamcakes Cafe with my mother and sister for afternoon tea. It was such a special day for us because we planned afternoon tea right before they accompanied me to shop for my wedding dress! The staff knew this and were so excited, kind, and encouraging.

We made our tea selections a few days before our event via email. Kallie was wonderful about responding on email. We had to sign a contract prior to the tea and she made it very easy to do so. When we arrived to the cafe, our tea table was set up with everything we needed: teacups, utensils, saucers, even fresh flowers! The set up was stunning and the food was delicious! I highly recommend the pimento cheese sandwich with peach jam and the macarons!!

During the tea, the wait staff made us feel so special. Someone was always by to ensure we had everything we needed, refill cups, etc and all of them were SO polite, friendly, and knowledgable about tea selections. My sister had a gluten and dairy allergy and they made sure she knew what she could and couldn't eat and even brought out a special cup of chicken salad for her.

Thank you Dreamcakes staff! You made this such a special day for us. The thought and time you put into the details of our tea was noticed and SO appreciated. It was perfect from start to finish. Hope to see yall again soon... we will be back!!

resp.text:
Thank you so much Erin! It was such a pleasure working with you. We really enjoyed serving you during your tea and are so happy that you enjoyed it so much! We are pleased to accommodate all allergies and love that we were able to find the best solution for your sister. We love going above and beyond for you customers! We look forward to seeing you in the future!

- Dreamcakes Cafe Staff

name: Kathy McLaurin
text: Good cupcakes! Was a little upset that I asked for a wedding cake cupcake and after arriving home, realized they gave me a vanilla cupcake instead. I’m not a fan of plain vanilla anyway, but I didn’t finish it- the frosting had a slight “soap” taste to it. For $5 a cupcake I’m not sure it was worth it. However, I loved the other flavors provided! My advice: don’t get the vanilla, and make sure you check to make sure you pay for the cupcakes you actually want! I would have gone back, but they were already closed and it’s a 15 minute drive from where I live.

text: I love the cinnamon fry dough cookie, and the heath bar one. The flavors change every week and most weeks they have at least one super yummy cookie. I never can figure out where you're supposed to park for pickup though.

name: RalphFLA
text:
This location of the Crumbl cookies store is relatively new. I was not familiar with it, saw it in the shopping center, researched it and thought it sounded like a good place to visit.

Crumbls has only been around since 2017. It appears to be growing fast.

At the end of a bike ride, I stopped to try it out. It was a good decision. Their cookies are excellent.

They are served warm. For cookies, they are expensive but these are better than any other cookies I have had in a store. The chocolate chips were tasty and large, the dough was warm and the cookies were fresh.

They are also very large. One cookie should be enough for two people. But, based on experience, many of us will eat a whole one.

The cookie flavors apparently vary each day. For those who have not done so, and who like to eat cookies, give Crumbls a try.

name: Craig Andrews
text: Grossly understaffed on a random Tuesday night. The staff managed the best that they could, but they needed more help. Ordering system must be difficult to manage because there was no rhyme or reason for some waiting 15 minutes and others waiting up to 45 minutes. Online orders seemed to be sprinkled in with those waiting in store. I will say the cookies were warm as promised and tasty but out of six flavors available, two were sold out. I would only go here again if there was nobody in the store waiting in line. At one point there were 25 people inside waiting on orders to be filled. Definitely not worth the wait.

name: Ryan Cass
text: Crumbl cookies knows how to make the perfect chocolate chip cookie and with easy touch screens to order and fast service gourmet cookies have never been so easy to get.

name: Caroline Meyers
text: By far the best cookies in town! I’ve loved every flavor I’ve tried. Both the Madison and JV location in Huntsville are clean and efficient! Love this addition to Huntsville!

name: A Ok
text: I enjoyed my first Crumbl Cookie experience this past Mother's Day, what a treat! My sister had brought these to celebrate our mother's day celebration, and we cut them all up into eight pieces so we could all try ANY type that we desired. You know, all of them. They were undoubtedly the best cookies EVER. We all loved them. They added an extra sweet something to our celebration. We rave about them to friends and coworkers. Thanks for all the different flavors that I have yet to try. Wonderful product, terrific Crumbl Cookies!

name: annie johnson
text: These cookies are amazing! Fresh out the oven. I love how they switch up the flavors.

name: Smore Spohrs
text: Good tasting cookies other than my dislike of almond flavoring in the icing on the sugar cookie. I'll avoid that cookie from now on. The milk chocolate chip was really good, with a good chip to cookie ratio, especially for someone who doesn't like chocolate. The Oreo cookie was fine, as was the blueberry cookie. No cookies that knocked my socks off, but good indeed. I'm willing to give then another try with a different menu. 😃

name: Laura Frame
text: Very pleased with our cookies! I think the rotating menu is an interesting idea. The waffle cookie was amazing! There was a bit of a wait, but understandable because it was the first Friday they were open. I'll order online for pickup next time because you basically do the same thing in the store.

name: Jolene Dean
text: I'm frequently disappointed by these cookies.. they look appealing in general.. but the base cookie recipe isn't great.  I definitely don't recommend using the app to order. I just waited over 30 minutes for my order only for them to tell me they were out of strawberries for the topping on the strawberries and cream cookie.

name: Jenn Armstrong
text: Went into the store, checked out the cookie options and my kids really wanted to try the German chocolate one. I know it normally has nuts in the cake. But there was no sign or info saying this one had. Made sure to ask the young lady that was helping us. She checked the ingredients and assured us it did NOT. I was thrilled. Drive back home and start eating the cookie. Then my throat starts to close up. Take a look at my "nut" free cookie and see walnuts. Called the store and brought up the issue so it wouldn't happen to someone deadly allergic and she practically brushed it off. Please start placing signs or info when a cookie contains nuts!

resp.text: Jenn, We apologize for the experience you had! We will pass this up to our team and they will look into your suggestions! Thank you for your feedback!

name: Jessalyn Davis
text: Seriously some of the best cookies I’ve tasted! Love how each week comes with new flavors to try!

name: B. Anders
text: Crumbl cookies makes some great cookies that taste as if they were made at home! The chocolate chip and chilled sugar are my absolute favorite! I’m thankful I live near one as cookies are my favorite dessert, but it’s also risky having one so close as they’re so delicious! I like that they change their flavors each week as well to keep the menu rotating and fresh!

text: These cookies are amazing!!! Highly addictive, highly recommend, and you gotta get em whenever you can. I mean why not? Different cookies every week to try, and they are so dang yum when they are still warm and gooey. Definitely shareable….remember sharing is caring. And these cookies will for sure put a smile on somebody’s face.

text: I had to come home and put my own condiments on my sandwich. And they weren’t even busy it was just me and my gf. So no excuse for this. I would give it a one star but I like the owner and she gets my order right and the other females there. But the incompetence of the male that works there is appalling. I’ve been there more than 10+ times to get a basic turkey and cheese sandwich with everything on it and of the 8 times the make has taken my order and what do I get a basic a** sandwich I could have made at home for way less and having to driving then getting my order wrong. How hard is it to make a sandwich with just meat and cheese a little mayo and mustard and lettuce. And to top it all off this sandwich is 5 dollars. Like wow. Like if you can’t make a sandwich how are you good at anything else. I love the restaurant and the other workers there, but the male with now highlights in his hair needs to be fired. It’s the reason I hate going when the owners or the all females staff isn’t there. Other than that I would rate this. 5 star but he makes it a 2.

resp.text: I am so very sorry!  I’ll make you a deal...come back in and see me, and I’ll treat you to lunch or dinner. I know how upsetting it can be to make it all the way home, tired and hungry, only to have your food be disappointing. We love good customers like you and want to make you happy. I look forward to seeing you very soon! —Suzanne

name: Margie Brooks
text: Just found Suzanne's today, awesome place, cake was so good, I will be back to try lunches!! Please support small business, give them a chance.

name: Joshua Hill
text: So, if you've not been on Thursday or Friday morning yet to try the Sun Drop rolls -- you're doing yourself a disservice. Very kind people and excellent service -- even at 6:30 in the morning. The Sun Drop rolls were warm, sweet and definitely unique. I can't wait to get back to try some others goodies!

name: Suzanne Peterson
text: This is not a bakery I would return to. First I went because of the name. Then I read the menu and it sounded great. I called to ask about breakfast and they were all out. Then I asked about breads and cinnamon rolls. I purchased a turtle bread which tasted ok. A little dry but edible. I then purchased a cinnamon roll and a drop roll. Both very dry and not a lot of flavor. I guess I will just make my own next time, they would taste better. I also bought a Danish. It tasted like it was made out of a biscuit. I would prefer to buy one from a grocery store. We also purchased a piece of red velvet cake. At least it wasn't dry but where is the cream cheese frosting? I may give it another chance if I were to try the chocolate peanut butter cake. Thanks but no thanks! I guess I will look around for another bakery.

name: Deluxe 09
text:
***I had to pick a "STAR".....this place doesn't deserve one****

I just called this "shop" and was going to see if I could order the Sun-drop rolls for pickup on Saturday morning. (It's Thursday)  Since I live in Nashville and will be in that area on Saturday....I thought no problem.  The guy who answered the phone was very pleasant and very helpful.  He had to ask if that would be okay....boy, I'm not sure who he asked,  maybe this Suzanne? But I can tell you I will NEVER be doing business with her or her shop.  She totally snapped on that little guy saying "NO, we are not taking any orders for Saturday."  I'm sure I can find a better recipe to make these Sun-drop rolls.....

name: Robert Hughes
text:
Consistently the worst experience.  Want a sandwich with tomatoes?  They're out of tomatoes.  Want a sandwich with cucumbers? Out of cucumbers.  What about a bagel sandwich with bacon?  Out of bagels and bacon.  How about customer service?  All out of that too. But there's plenty of awful selection and rude attitude directed at their customers.

I ordered a bagel sandwich with bacon, the were out of bagels, and got no bacon.  I went back to ask about my missing bacon and was rudely told "We don't have no bacon", then the employee stormed off.  I will forego lunch and drive off campus from now on; no more 3-4x weekly visits to this awful place.

name: Luan Brashaw
text: I have recently moved to the area and Publix is a brand that is familiar and trusted. Publix at The Bray is like all Publix, friendly, polite team members waiting to help with a smile. This fairly new store offers all the same grocery brands and deals as my "old" Publix. I was delighted to find a self-serve hot bar and salad bar in addition to their deli. I believe they even have a seating area upstairs.  All employees were masked which is becoming more unusual since the COVID vaccine has become more available to the general public. Well-lit, amply spaced aisles add to the overall pleasant shopping experience. I look forward to frequenting this store AND the shopping complex it is a part of while I live in this area.

I get to the register with my 4 pack and they ring up normal price. I ask about. A young lady goes and checks then comes back and tells me it only for the bigger packs. Then why is it on all the pack sizes? They must of run out of room is what I am told. The cashier was very nice, apologetic but the other lady although not rude was not willing to solve the issue but was insistent on me paying full price. Needless to say although I would normally just pay decided not too and left. This was not a customer mistake but store level which should of been handled better.

text: I bought this at Sam’s Club in Montgomery, Al thinking they were a decent size (about a large slice of cake) and would be around $3-$4/slice. It didn’t have a price  on it and now I know why. It rang up $7.50!.. for a slice of cake?!? So, I gave it the benefit of the doubt and brought it home, eager to eat it for dessert. Red Velvet “snack” is on the label. Red velvet is my favorite cake and I’ve never had a bad one.. until now! It tasted like more of a tart, lemon flavored sweet cake than my normal fav.  Don’t waste your money! I wouldn’t buy this for a quarter of the price. I’m very disappointed. Emily’s, if you make a deal with a large box store like Sam’s Club, especially for way overpriced cake, make it good! I’m giving this a one star because of price and taste. What else is there to judge about cakes?? Trust me, do yourself a favor and avoid this brand.

resp.text:
Good evening Justin - I'm extremely sorry you didn't enjoy the cake. The cakes are all butter, gourmet & all natural ingredients which are expensive. Let me start by saying the Snack cakes are 8.5 oz and our slices are 4 oz.  This means the Snack cakes are double the size of our 1" thick slices. Also, the prices are shown above the cakes. The cost of the Red Velvet (specialty cake with creamcheese butter cream is actually $8.98 in Sam's Club not $7.48. The $7.48 cakes are non specialty flavors (Original, Lemon Blueberry, Key Lime & Chocolate). It sounds like there is a problem. We stand behind all of our product and I'd really appreciate if you would send a picture of the packaging and inside of the cake, if possible. We will ship you a replacement as we know our cakes are worthy and some of the BEST in the business. Please email us @ emilyshpc@gmail.com and we will gladly get to the bottom and rectify the issue. Enjoy your weekend  sir!

April

name: Stew Hayles III
text:
Took my dog to the Barkery in October 2020. It was z horrible experience.  I blame myself because I waited until the last minute to make a boarding appointment at my usually facility, which is Golden Animal Hospital in Pike Road(great service and care everytime!). We boarded our 18 month old golden doodle for 10 days. He was supposed to be groomed the last day he was there. We keep his hair long so he was only supposed to be washed and trimmed.

When I dropped him off, the receptionist was nice enough but the place smelled very bad. I've used several dog care facilities since we're new to Montgomery and the Bakery was by far the worst in cleanliness.  The dogs and the administration area are all in one. This created a very unorganized check-in since the receptionist was moving, picking up and pushing dogs off the counter the entire check-in. I looked over this because we were literally flying out of town the same day.

10 days later, I called to the Barkery know I was headed to pick my dog up. They told me that they had to cut his hair down low because he had a few matted areas on his legs. I didn't like that but its understandable. I arrive to the counter and the owner hands me a bag of hair to "prove" how bad the matts were! They brought my dog out and he was literally shaved down to skin😥 It was so sad! They didn't even grind or clip his nails. It was clear that they had no clue what they were doing. They couldn't find his collar and leash. They said that I must have taken it with me. I usually take them with me at my normal grooming place but I thought I remembered leaving them. I didn't take the time to debate the point because I was almost numb at the sight of my dog. I just kept telling myself, "This is your fault for waiting too long to make an appointment and taking him to the ONLY place that had an opening" Now I know why they had an opening. For the life of me, I can not figure out how people are giving this place good reviews.

When I get home and the family and I console each other, lol.....I find my dogs collar and flea collar buried in his door food that I had left with the Barkery. My dog also wouldn't eat for days after we got him back and he was sick for at least a week. He sneezing and vomiting. Btw, he smelled horrible. I was trying to figure out what they used to wash him and if they actually bathed him the day before I picked him up.

This was the worst experience ever and I would learn to groom my own dog if this was the only place open. On top of all of this, the receptionist and owner never apologized for the haircut. They basically blamed me because I let him get matts.

Worst experience ever!

name: Jonathan Bowman

He absolutely loves going now and tries to fight me to leave. I cannot say enough amazing things about this place!

name: Alexandria Harvest
text: Pet Parents BEWARE! On July 2, I dropped my dog Midnight off at The Barkery, we planned to go out of town, so we let the staff member know that we would want to do daycare and boarding, because we planned to go out of town and would be back late. We ended up not going out of town, so my sister called The Barkery  at 5:35 to inform them that we would not be boarding and we were coming to pick midnight up, she said okay, everything seemed normal. My sister got to The Barkery 6 minutes later and call and through tears told me that the Barkery allowed my dog to get out of their gate, around 5:00pm,  THIRTY MINUTES AGO. Apparently Haley the staff worker, did not want to upset her and tell her over the phone. Mind you, they thought we were boarding, and at no point did they reach out to either Emergency contact listed on the paperwork, had my sister not unexpectedly showed up, it looks like they had no plan to reach out. We were told that Haley was in one room(making mop water), and Kimberly the owner was in another room(cleaning) while the dogs were outside, and unattended. They heard a loud noise, and a customer who was coming to pick up their dog came in and informed them that a black dog with a blue collar had gotten out. They had no idea because they weren't watching. One Hour later, me and my siblings were out looking for my dog with NO ASSISTANCE from The Barkery.  No one called either of Midnight's listed emergency contacts,  reached out to establish a perimeter, or even apologize and explain what happened. I had to reach out to Kimberly and request that she call me via text. When she did call, she did not apologize, she simply blamed us because he jumped the fence, all while not looking for my dog that she lost. My dog has been coming to the barkery since they were on Woodley rd, and he's never jumped. Around 7 I went back to Barkery, and Kim

name: Kaleigh Culver
text: My yorkie,Oscar stayed all week for boarding while we went out of town for work and he loved it so much I didn’t think he was gonna leave and come back home to me!!! Stopped and got him a pup a chino afterwards:) We will definitely be back! Thankful to find someone I can trust with my fur baby! Thanks to,Kimberly and staff @TheBarkery

text: My experience with the whole staff was absolutely amazing, they took care & loved my baby Rue.

name: Micheal Waters
text: Ordered a birthday cake from The Barkery. They had it ready the same day and my dog absolutely loved it!

name: Patricia Macon
text: My dog Lucy goes here for daycare and grooming and she gets so excited whenever we arrive. She always looks and smells so good whenever she gets groomed with Kim!!

name: Greg Hooper
text: Hands down would never take my dogs anywhere else. My dogs are ecstatic to come in and never want to come home!

name: Kim Tomberlin
text: You can really see how much they care for the fur baby clients and their parents. Their treatments are amazing, they do baths, messages, hair removal brushes them so well and does all styles and sizes  of grooming.  I was very happy to see when you board your fur babies they have someone there  with them  24 hours a day . That means so much to me. They make wonderful treats from scratch that look so good and healthy. I know that mine will be there quite often. You can trust that when you take your fur child there they get the best care possible!

name: Zovi “Zovi” V
text: Pet Parents BEWARE! On July 2, I dropped my dog Midnight off at The Barkery, we planned to go out of town, so we let the staff member know that we would want to do daycare and boarding, because we planned to go out of town and would be back late. We ended up not going out of town, so my sister called The Barkery  at 5:35 to inform them that we would not be boarding and we were coming to pick midnight up, she said okay, everything seemed normal. My sister got to The Barkery 6 minutes later and call and through tears told me that the Barkery allowed my dog to get out of their gate, around 5:00pm,  THIRTY MINUTES AGO. Apparently Haley the staff worker, did not want to upset her and tell her over the phone. Mind you, they thought we were boarding, and at no point did they reach out to either Emergency contact listed on the paperwork, had my sister not unexpectedly showed up, it looks like they had no plan to reach out. We were told that Haley was in one room(making mop water), and Kimberly the owner was in another room(cleaning) while the dogs were outside, and unattended. They heard a loud noise, and a customer who was coming to pick up their dog came in and informed them that a black dog with a blue collar had gotten out. They had no idea because they weren't watching. One Hour later, me and my siblings were out looking for my dog with NO ASSISTANCE from The Barkery.  No one called either of Midnight's listed emergency contacts,  reached out to establish a perimeter, or even apologize and explain what happened. I had to reach out to Kimberly and request that she call me via text. When she did call, she did not apologize, she simply blamed us because he jumped the fence, all while not looking for my dog that she lost. My dog has been coming to the barkery since they were on Woodley rd, and he's never jumped. Around 7 I went back to Barkery, and Kimberly and her significant other, Jake arrived( how she had time to go get her boyfriend while she claimed she was looking for my dog, not sure). Kimberly ran inside the building, never spoke, never apologized and sent Jake, who is not an owner of The Barkery,  to "deal" with us. Apparently, Kimberly had lied to Jake and told him that she was threatened by myself on the phone and was called a b****h, which was untrue, I was actually quite pleasant all considered. When Kimberly finally came outside, I asked her was she ever threaten or called any obscenity and she said no that never happened. Jake went off to smoke his KOOL cigarette, because the whole reason he came was because of her lie.Why Kimberly would make herself to be the victim when she lost my dog is beyond me. Kimberly yelled us, blamed us,  cursed, and never once apologized. I understand that things happen, but if you're a dog sitter and you lose the dog, you need to take some form of responsibility and at least be sorry and try to help. Instead of being concerned,  Kimberly(owner) and her daughter, and another staff member keep screaming about their "Livelihood".  Thankfully, me and my family were able to go out looking at 6:00 am and posting lost posters and found Midnight near Huntingdon College. The staff members saw us looking for our dog, offered no help, and still no apology.  Today is July 9, and The Barkery has never followed up, or showed any concern for their negligence. My dog refuses to leave me or my sisters side since this event, so I'd advise you to find another place to drop off your four legged family member.

name: Tim Watts
text: I witnessed the entire staff act in a rude and extremely unprofessional manner . The entire staff allowed my sister's dog, Midnight, to walk away from the facility due to the staff not regularly monitoring the outside activities of the animals. Furthermore, they waited until a family member arrived at the facility to pick up the dog instead of calling the emergency contacts to notify of the situation, approximately 30 minutes after Midnight ran off. The owner, Kimbery, argued with us, accused us of calling her a derogatory term, admitted she lied about being called a derogatory term, and then refused to look for the dog. This incident occurred on Thursday, July 2nd. Today is July 5th and we have yet to hear from Kimberly on the status of the search for our dog. I highly recommend that you look elsewhere for your dog sitting needs.

name: Shantel Stewart
text: There is no doubt that there are plenty of boarding and grooming places to go to in Montgomery.  HOWEVER, The Barkery has a staff that is loving and caring.  I have been going here for about 6 years.  The staff is unbelievably loving and caring.  They become emotional attached to your dogs and become your friend.  Kim, Steve, and Sydni are all so very sweet.  If your dog is not the playful type, then they may not like this place.  The Barkery has a very dog friendly natural playful atmosphere where all of the dogs get to be dogs!  They get to play and socialize with one another and get treats and loved on by the staff.  Every dog owner is particular in their own way and that's understanding.  But despite them being our fur children, they are still dogs and want to play with one another and run around.  If you want your dog to have fun and be loved and for you to feel secure knowing that they are safe, then the Barkery is the place to go!!  I'll never go elsewhere.  My dog instantly gets excited the moment we pull up and is eager to run inside.  That lets me know that they too love going there.  And don't get me started on how amazing they smell when they get groomed.  As silly as it sounds, I could smell my dog all day after they get groomed.  I LOVE THE BARKERY!!!!

name: John Clark
text: Kim is awesome. I love that I can leave my Sophie and not worry. She always has a good time.

name: Jacoby Pace
text: Hands down the most unprofessional and inconsiderate group of people when it comes to the care of your four legged family member. Would not recommend!!!!

name: HALEY MCDONALD
text: I cannot stress enough how important it is to take care of your dog to the best of your ability. That’s why I take my dog here. I know that my dog is getting the best treatment and the best care here with Kim and the other staff. I strongly recommend taking your dog here!

text: The Barkery is and amazing place for fur babies they treat all the clients well and try to fit you in even when the packed. I would trust my dogs there more than anywhere else in montgomery and not to mention my dog is in love with there hand made treats this place is an all in one you should definitely think twice before going somewhere else.
