text: Always friendly. Always good food! Try a kolache, they are amazing.

name: Hunter Wilsford
text: Had the awesome bacon topped donut from an assortment at work and was lucky to get that before I think 3 dozen were completely gone!

name: Michael Talley
text: Such a great place! Super friendly, super tasty.

name: essence phenix
text: Fast and friendly service! The doughnuts were amazing!! Can’t wait to go back!

name: stephanie k
text: Delicious donuts and great customer service!

name: Tim spradlin
text: Great donuts and service

name: Edward Parsons
text: It's good! Remember napkins for your face.😁🤙🍩☕

name: Dale Mccrackin
text: Great food and awesome service!

name: Mel Ann
text: High price and low taste.

name: Sarah Fields
text: Super friendly service and fresh, yummy doughnuts. Will be back!!

name: Tamara Jenkins
text: Great  service  and great food.

name: Shane Jones
text: Great service and the best donuts.

name: Joshua Wallace
text: Best place in state

name: Amy Wyatt
text: Yummy doughnuts 🍩😍😁

name: Tiffany Baker
text: Great food!!! Great People!!!!

name: Josh Meil
text: Amazing!

name: Jay Clyce
text:
Where do I start?  This small business is a delight.  I believe this is such a fun place because all of the different types of cupcakes.  They have something for EVERY occasion.  They are so yummy and fun at the same time.

Do you need to treat a friend, family member, colleague or client?  If they like something sweet, this is the place.

Don’t wait.  Reward yourself or someone you want to provide a smile to.  Go NOW!!!

name: Grant Langbauer
text: When driving 14+ hours, one must stop for a Gigis Cupcake(s)

name: shandrita foster
text: Delicious as always!

name: Christy Holden
text: So many great options to choose from! I love the mini cupcakes because they provide just the right amount of sweetness. Conveniently located and can be packaged up safely to take home if you want to share with friends!

name: Rikesha Foster
text: Pretty good cupcakes. Are they anything to write mom about? Not necessarily. They are pretty on the outside, but as far as taste-wise, they are average cupcakes. Nothing more, nothing less. But give them a try.

name: MO Mules
text: Not the freshest, they were dry and overcooked..frosting was great. Maybe an off day for baking? Not sure but cake was tossed. Nice little shop and worker.

name: Sandra Accardi
text: The perfect sweet treat for a quick gift or just indulging your sweet tooth. The 2-size option is very helpful when my different moods require different levels of sweetness. Great variety of flavors!

name: David Carter
text: As a Pharmaceutical Representative, we are always looking to separate ourselves from our competitor. So, I am very reluctant to reveal this hidden jewel. The cakes and cupcakes are excellent! My customers always look forward to treats from Gigi's! As a rep they are very easy to work with and the customer service is second to none!

name: Bill Tiemann
text: This is a great place to pick up a gourmet cupcake. The cake is light and fluffy and the buttercream frosting is over the top. Highly recommended.

name: J Hanson
text: We have only had good experiences with Gigi's!  We have placed several large orders as gifts and Gigi's is always so helpful.  Their customer service is beyond excellent and they make it all so easy for us.  We will definitely continue ordering from Gigi's!

name: Eric S
text: I agree with those posting overrated.  I don't know why we keep buying from this place.  Loaded with tons of sugar on the top and the actual cake part is never really as good as you could make at home.  I could make 12 for the price of one.  Got 3 s'mores tonight and the cake was a bit stale and not very good.  In addition the receipt has a line to leave a tip.  Are you kidding me?  At nearly $4 per cupcake, they need to pay their staff more and not ask me for tip for someone reaching into a cabinet and putting a cupcake in a box.  It's a bit over the top.  I don't plan to buy any more cupcakes from there.

name: Racheal Day
text: I waited years to try GiGi's. I wasn't mind blown. They we're good but nothing special and I had to cut the icing in half.

name: Sweetpee Learning from ground Zero using my press
text: Everything was great treats and service...I hate the state the company is in...bc they have great cupcakes 😋

name: Ju Mc
text: Great cupcakes but will be permanently closing on 31MAR19.

name: James R. Landrum
text: Pleasant staff. The cupcakes didn't really suit my tastes, but I'm not huge on icing. The stuffed cookies are actually very good, though.

name: Manley Whittier
text: After eating Gigi's cupcakes many times and loving them, I was very disappointed this past Friday night. I went in your establishment after dinner and saw the Salted Caramel Chocolate cupcakes and had to try them as I love just about anything salted caramel. I also got a Sundae cupcake too. After getting home, my wife and I tried to eat the cupcakes and they tasted old and somewhat burnt. Do you bake your cupcakes fresh daily or do you keep them for sale until they are gone? We ended up throwing out what we didn't eat. I hope your quality is not going down but if I go there again and have a similar experience I will not return.

name: Bree Sison
text: I love this place probably a little too much.  Always delicious & super appreciate their military discount!

name: David McDonald
text: GiGi's Hoover catered my wedding. They were affordable, professional and most of all delicious!! We had bourbon maple cupcakes and champagne cupcakes along with a white cake with butter cream frosting for us to cut. The managers/owners Jason and Cheryl Vinyard were awesome to work with and I would easily recommend them for any occasion big or small.

name: Celeste Cohill
text: I ordered one of the lemon. The icing was delicious but the cake just didn't deliver at all.

name: Hope Heath Cox
text: GiGi's cupcakes catered my wedding cake, grooms cake, and mini cupcakes for my wedding and I am still in awe of the wonderful job that they did. I would encourage all brides in the Birmingham area to go for a tasting and you will not be disappointed. I had about 5 tastings with the most popular wedding cake bakers in the area and while they were all good, the cake at GiGi's out-tasted everyone! Not many people realize that they also offer full-size wedding cakes and not just cupcakes. I had a brunch wedding and went to taste the cinnamon roll cake that I had heard was fantastic (was actually recommended by my caterer, Kathy G). Wow, it was phenomenal!! The Chocolate grooms cake was just as tasty. I had a tight window that in which I needed the cake delivered and set up since I was having my ceremony and reception at the same place. They went out of there way to get it there in time and set up... it was absolutely perfect. Honestly the best tasting cakes I have ever had at a wedding and my guests agreed. They were also beautifully decorated! Bravo, GiGi's!

resp.text:
Hope,

Thank you so much for your wonderful comments.  It was our pleasure to share a part of your special day.

name: j milwood
text: Always a good experience and great variety offered. Kudos to the employees for always being friendly.

name: Toni Williams
text: My daughter wanted to try a Gigi's cupcake so bad, so what a perfect time to surprise her with one since she had been sick.  The the store itself is decorated beautifully, but the customer service did not match.  Since this was my first time in the store I had a lot of questions and the young lady that was assisting me really acted like, 'would you just buy a cupcake please."  I did not know what to buy so I bought 5 different kinds.  And they are wayyyyyyy to sweet, they are loaded with frosting but I thought they would have cut back on the sugar, but that was not the case. The cake stuck to the cupcake wrapper and , the boxes they put them in are beautiful but don't close all the way so the air made them hard 3 hours after I bought them.  I was really disappointed.  Not to mention the 5 I bought were almost 16.$ I would have saved money and enjoyed cupcakes from Publix better.

name: Ally D.
text: The cupcakes were really tasty. I always thought it was a little bit pricy but it was worth it. I really hope I didn't eat the one with the fly landed on..

name: Crystal Brophy
text:
SO OVERRATED!
Not a really good cupcake honestly.
Publix bakery cupcakes are 10x better!
Over rated, over priced & over iced!
I do not know why people insist on saying, "You must have a GiGi's cupcake, they are the best"! Because in my book and many people that I know agree, that they are FAR from the best.
The cake part is moist, but not that flavorful and they overdo the frosting bigtime. I could frost 3 cupcakes with the amount they put on 1 cupcake.
Not good at all.
Sorry GiGi's, you are not a top notch bakery.
SOURCE: Bought a strawberry cupcake from GiGi's a few years back and wasn't thrilled at all, specially for the price. Since then, I have had about 4 more (ones that people have had at parties and such) and I just ate a chocolate one like 10 minutes ago, every single one was the same, not good.

name: Hannah maddox
text: I loved going to GiGis kiosk in the mall because I loved the little blonde girl who worked there! So sweet and always have great conversation! I was so sad to hear that she was fired for "customer  dissatisfaction." Very very confused GiGis!!! :(

name: Connie Settles
text: We ordered the turtle cheesecake....overloaded on sugar and not very tasty. We did not enjoy these!

name: Micahel Shavers
text: Good cupcakes, prices are a bit high, but of good quality and taste.

name: Amanda Miniard
text: Came for my free birthday cupcake and they put a candle in it for me!  What a great way to make someone feel special!

name: Rosanna Dale
text: Great customer service and good Cupcakes!

name: Valerie H
text: Better than one in Trussville.  Still too expensive.

name: Janet McDonald
text: Employee was rude when I asked about coupon I had from clipper magazine. You would have thought that I had asked for a free item! I won’t be doing business here until staff has a bit of training in customer service!

resp.text: Hi Janet, all I can say is WOW!! I am so sorry this happened to you.  We have those coupons published for our guests to use.  This is totally unacceptable behavior and it won't be tolerated.  Please give us a call so we can get some information from you about your experience.  205-444-4170. Please ask for Cheryl.

name: Sheila Brown
text: Cupcakes are delicious!

name: Ashleigh
text: Great!

name: Brenna Marshall
text: Best gluten-free cupcakes ever!

name: Angela Yancy
text: Laura went out of her way to make sure our cake matched our invitations, plus there was a sugar free option, too!! This makes the third time that Blissfully Sweet has exceeded my expectations. I cannot wait until my next cake order!

name: Kim Eller
text: I have used this business twice and both times the employees have gone above and beyond. I had them make my daughters black cake with a skull and she was so excited over it we had to force her to cut it. My sons 21st birthday is coming up in a week and I'm looking forward to  seeing the work these ladies do on it.  Thank you! Excellent job! Need something stop and just see what they can do!

name: Jack Morris
text: Blissfully Sweet ' s baked goods are amazing and their customer service is incredible.  I would highly recommend this bakery to anyone!!!

Walked in two hours before closing, looking for some cute cookies for my sons engagement the next day!  They went above and beyond making some beautiful "bride and groom" cookies that were delicious!
Thank you for your help!  We WILL be back!

resp.text: Thank you! We're glad you enjoyed them! Hope to see you soon! And thank you for the pic

name: david mayer
text: Just picked up my wedding cake and I absolutely love it! It is definitely one of the most beautiful cakes I've ever seen! I highly recommend this place!

resp.text: Congrats! We are happy to help,with your special day. Thank you!

name: iris terrio
text:
These ladies are amazing.  They made a wedding cake in a few hours after the one I brought from New Orleans was broken while transporting it. The cake was perfect and our son had new daughter -in- law loved it.

Thank you very much for getting the cake ready on such short notice.

resp.text: Happy to help! So happy, you were pleased! Thank you and congratulations.

name: Billie McCoy
text: Oh my word!! Wonderful!!!

resp.text: Thank you! We love our bakery!

name: Donna Ham
text: My daughters had a 60th birthday celebration for me and these ladies made me the perfect Black Forest cake...my favorite!! It’s so hard to find that cake made the way it should be.  Everyone loved the cake and said it was the best they’d ever eaten. Thank you so much!!!

name: Robin Hall
text: We had an awesome experience with Coastal Cakes and Confections!!  I had to make all of the arrangements over the phone to purchase a 15th birthday cake for my daughter's beach trip with her friends. Her best friend helped pick her 'Harry Styles' cake out and it was definitely a custom order cake. They went above and beyond making sure everything was taken care of for us to surprise my daughter. The price was more than fair! This cake was moist & yummy even after we got it back home and refrigerated the unused portion. Icing was great too! We are very picky since I also make cakes but since we were traveling this year, I wanted to surprise her by trying out this bakery.  Not one bite of cake was wasted and I will definitely use them again if traveling in the future. The bakery itself is also so clean & just precious! We were very impressed by the service recieved and would give them more stars if possible! Dont hesitate to let them help you out for you bakery needs! The only regret we have is not ordering some iced cookies too. They looked so yummy! Thank you ladies so much for helping us pull off my daughter's bday cake surprise! She absolutely LOVED it and we have had tons of compliments on all the pics of it we have both shared on social media accounts.

resp.text: Oh my gosh! Such a nice review! We are so pleased that you were this happy with your cake! We appreciate your feedback.

name: Robert Reynolds
text: I decided to choose a small 5’ birthday cake that was just delicious...The staff was very helpful and professional reminding me of days gone by of someone who really knows their stuff.. Give them a visit. You will be glad you did!!!!

resp.text: Thank you so much for the kind words! We appreciate it! Have a wonderful day!

name: Brandy Pickett
text: This place is Heaven!!!! They captured the idea I needed and amplified it! They were very respectful and professional. They can create cakes with pictures (hard to find those places) all the way to zombie cakes with a hand sticking out. Their store is very clean and fresh smelling. So glad I went to them. This is my second cake and I trust them! I will forever be a client!

name: Brandon Styles Live
text: This is a great family owned and operated bakery with friendly staff. We visit a few times each year to make dessert platters for work and gifts

resp.text: Thank you! We really appreciate your business! Hope to see you again soon. We love our bakery 🧁

name: Kathy Terry
text: Ordered a Halloween themed cake for our grown daughter. I explained what I wanted, cakes like I got as a child, also being a October 29 baby, I wanted those memories for her. Boy did you nail it. Loved the witch flying thru moon. You couldn't have done any better. Thank you, and by the way the cake was the BEST, VERY DELICIOUS and Perfect icing. Gonna order another one this week for my birthday to share with grandkids ♥️ will be recommending you when I can

resp.text: We are so pleased that you liked the cake! Thank you for the nice review. Hope to see you soon.

name: Traci Wright
text: I had a cake made for my son's 21st birthday. I wasn't sure exactly what I wanted but they took the time to talk to me and share ideas with me. The design they came up with was perfect! And the cake tasted amazing! I will definitely be having all cakes made here from now on!

resp.text: Thank you so much! Glad your were pleased! We love our bakery. Hope to see you soon.

text:
Crazy delicious! We got a unicorn cupcake for our bday girl and different kinds of brownies. It all tastes amazing! We are going back to try their cookies which look super tempting.
They were extremely nice, attentive and welcoming.

Definitely recommend for a tasty treat.

resp.text: Thank you! Glad you enjoyed your treats. Hope to see yall again

name: Shana Brooke Wheeler
text: Coastal cakes was absolutely perfect! I had a special request for a 30th birthday cake and boy did they deliver! The cake was EXACTLY what I imagined and tasted even better than I could have expected! The pick up was easy and quick! If I ever need another cake when at the coast, Coastal Cakes and Confections will be my go-to!

resp.text: Awww, thank you so much! Were glad you were pleased. We appreciate the review. Hope to see you again!

name: Andrea King
text: The most amazing bakery and deli I have every experienced in my life time . Thank you .

name: Tina Lamb
text:
Always worth the trip. Love the fresh squeezed OJ and danish's.
Fantasy cakes a little pricy for me but worth it for special occasion.

resp.text: Sorry, you have the wrong bakery, we do not have these items

name: Serendipity Art
text: I ordered a special birthday cake from Coastal bakery. I requested banana flavored cake. This is the first place I have found in 18 years to make a banana cake. It was the moistest, most tasteful cake I’ve ever had and eaten! The decorations were Coastal with a palm tree and seashells made of decedent white chocolate.  would highly recommend Coastal Bakery!

resp.text: Thank  so much for the wonderful review! So happy you enjoyed!!

name: Chuck Bossom
text: Best wedding cakes, pastries and tasty treats

resp.text: Thank you so much!

name: Caroline Hubbard
text: Thank you so much for my beautiful and delicious birthday cake. You went out of your way to help my boyfriend surprise me with the perfect cake!

resp.text: Aww, so happy you enjoyed it! We appreciate you review. Hope it was a perfect day!

name: Cologne Trooper
text: I ordered cat themed cupcakes last minute and they pulled through and exceeded my expectations! Love this place.

name: Slavko Djukic
text: Wonderful service and an even better cake. They helped us with our last minute wedding ceremony after we called just 2 days before it and helped making our special day perfect.

name: Glenda Sickles
text:
We needed a welcome gift for our condo guests...Coastal Cakes put together a delightful plate of cookies and bars.  It was exactly what we
wanted.  The cookies were delicious (we took some home for ourselves, of course!) and the price was reasonable.  We can totally recommend
this bakery for your sweet treats.

resp.text: Thank you so much! It was a pleasure meeting you both! We were happy to help! Hope to see you again soon.

name: Emma Hubbard
text: Beautiful cake for my parents 50th anniversary! They were able to make it gluten free, which was fantastic for some family members with Celiac.

resp.text: Glad to help! Hope to see you again. Thank you for the review!

name: Rhonda Martinez
text: I have been buying cookies and cup cakes from here since they opened. They are the best around. My daughter got married last month and we got her wedding cake from here also. The cake was absolutely amazing in looks, flavor and moisture. My daughter had her birthday this month and ask for another cake just like her wedding cake but smaller so we got it, another delicious, beautiful and moist cake. I am ordering another for my sons birthday this week. Absolutely love this place and the ladies are super sweet! Thank you Coastal Cakes

resp.text: Thank you so much for supporting us in our first year! And for the kind words! We love our new business and our wonderful customers!

name: Amy Russell
text: The best tasting cake and most beautiful cake we have ever had. The store is beautiful. The owners are incredibly talented.

resp.text: Thank you! So happy you were pleased! We are all sisters here and we love our bakery

name: pam johnson
text: I have been coming to Gulf Shores for over 20 years,  now I live here.  So thankful to find a great go to bakery. They are the best. Highly reccomend.

resp.text: Thank you so very much! We love our bakery, and our customers!

name: Mary Kay Charbonneau
text: I am from the UP of Mi and I found this treasure of a place. I recommend this place highly. I had the best coconut bars and the most delicious cupcakes. German chocolate and red velvet, but the cakes they make our great. They make beautiful wedding cakes. Please check this Amazing place out. I usually don't give reviews, but had to for this place.

name: Del Ray Brosdahl
text:
We ordered a birthday cake for our daughter's birthday. We described what we wanted. They told us about their secret recipe for a special cake. We ordered it and we were not disappointed. It was the very best cake we have had in many, many years .The only problem was we didn't order a bigger cake. We found a place for all of our future bakery needs.

DelRay Brosdahl

resp.text: We are so pleased you liked your cake! It is our all time favorite! Thank you so much for the nice review!

name: amandajs21
text: Such a great bakery! Sweet staff! Very accommodating. I asked for them to recreate my parents 30th anniversary cake for our trip to gulf shores. They did an amazing job and it was SO good!!

resp.text: Thank you! For the wonderful review!  So glad to help! We love what we do!

name: Tonya Love
text: We had the best visit in the Gulf Shores celebrating my dads 70th Birthday! We found the perfect coconut bars for my dad! We enjoyed meeting the sisters, we will definitely be back!😊

name: Shana Bell
text: Fun cakes and cookies,  super sweet staff!

name: Brandi Shrewsbury
text: I got my wedding and groom's cake from here. She gave me very reasonable prices compared to everywhere else. She even called me the day before to check and make sure the order was correct. They also delivered and had the cakes here on time. Also the cakes were amazing! I couldn't of asked for better service. I highly recommend using them.

name: Virginia Hiltibrand
text: We were married in Gulf Shores and they made Cupcakes and they were delicious.  The icing was not.too sweet and the cake was very moist.  The best cupcakes I ever had.  Thank you for making our day special.

name: Patti Bergstrom
text: Ordered a cake for my friends birthday and they went above and beyond. Beautiful cake with everything I mentioned on it. Absolutely beautiful and delicious, moist and everyone loved the light whipped frosting. I ordered a half sheet, half chocolate and half white. I thought we had too much cake, because it was huge. Everyone  who tried the chocolate, had to try the white and vice a verse, because it was so good! Great Job Coastal Cakes! We know where our birthday cakes will come from!!

name: Lindsay Gass
text: Stopped in today to pick up a last minute Bday cake and these ladies were so sweet!  They had a cake available and was able to make the cutest cake for a special bday.  I will make a stop to visit these ladies every time I make it to Gulf Shores now.

name: Kaitlyn Pope
text: What a great find! Coastal Cakes had the most delicious mexican wedding cake cookies. They melt in your mouth! They went out of their way to make a special mermaid tail for on top of my cupcake that was so cute, and tasted even better! The sisters who run it are delightful and friendly. We found our bakery in Gulf Shores! We wouldn’t think of going anywhere else!

name: Lemora Elliot
text: On vacation at Turquoise Place celebratiing my 64 birthday wirh my twin sister,!  Family ordered  a birthday  cake from Coastal Cakes and Confections! THE BEST BIRTHDAY CAKE I EVER HAD! Love Orange Beach, Turquoise Place, and Coastal Cakes and Confections

name: Billy/Tina Taylor
text: Excellent homemade cookies, cakes, and pastries. Employees and owner went above and beyond to do a very large Christmas cookie order. They were beautiful and “melt in your mouth delicious”!

resp.text: Thank You we enjoyed helping you with your order.

name: E Champ
text: The sisters were great. Did my little girl's birthday cupcakes in less the a day.  The buttercream icing was delicious!  We also got the cookies with icing. They reminded me of my nanny's teacakes.

name: Valerie Archer
text: I cannot say enough raving compliments about the kindness Costal Cakes shared with us to treat my Mother-in-law on vacation! This team maneuvered address issues, unresponsive recipients and changes to plan with grace and thoughtful action to save the day and we are so grateful!

resp.text: We were happy to help with this special day!

text:
If this is the one next to marcos pizza this is in my opinion the best dunkin donuts they dont get my order wrong and they always make my coffee just the way i like it and the customer service is great!!!
Just want to clarify that I'm talking about the Dunkin Donuts across from southeast hospital Best one very clean and friendly.

name: POP N PRETTY
text: I love this location trust me the area is convenient for me. As far as customer service they are very apologetic and decent customer service.Now food quality is complete trash they will burn your bread and pack it anyway hoping you overlook tire black bread, the hot drinks are hit and miss,specialty drinks always a miss. Mangers will redo the mistakes but it's too often for me.

name: Danielle Rae
text: I really wanted to love this Dunkin. It’s so convenient being across the street from my job. It was great when it first opened, but it’s TERRIBLE now. By mid day, there’s hardly a selection for donuts. Staff is rude to customers and they argue amongst each other right in front of customers. I’ve never had an issue with the RCC store, I guess I’ll just go there from now on.

name: Melissa Parker
text: Horrible. Out of every item except donuts however I didn’t order one. Turn left out a sandwich I drive to this location bc the first location was also out of items. Just stopped on our trip back home from the beach when I checked the bag it was missing 1 of 3 croissants ordered. I called and the male employee actually argued with me and said he personally made them. You may have made them but you didn’t deliver them. He hung up on me. Of course it’s rated 2.7 stars.

name: Dylan Patterson
text: Wanted to give 5 stars, but couldn't one of our latter's today was lukewarm and they were both supposed to be hot.

name: Patricia Rogers
text: Slowly getting better. Mornings around 7:30-8 they're packed out the wazoo!

name: cottonwood rescue
text:
Dunkin' let me tell y’all about the team at 1865 E. Main St. Dothan😍 This team is always the most friendly and helpful I have ever experienced at Dunkin’💯 & I have visited them from Panama City Beach to Tallahassee, to Birmingham to Gainesville & no other compares to my home store!🤞🏼As an Emt I’m on the go with 911 ALL day & believe me we are blazing the roads all day to and from the hospital. & I know if I need a pick me up I will only stop at this location. They know how to get my coffee fix prompt and exactly how I like it. 90% of the time they see me pull up on the ambulance and they already have my order going before I make it in the store! I know they have to be tired of seeing me but they always greet me with a smile on their faces! I couldn’t ask for better service and great personalities!  It’s the “Be safe out there today.” For me! 🥲 Y’all are just as essential as I am and I thank y’all for your service!  & keep being great!☺️

With much love always!💕☕️

- a very great full EMT🚑💙

name: Harley Wambles
text: Got there when they were supposed to be open this morning at 5, waited 10 minutes in the drive thru before checking the front of the store and seeing that no one was even there.

name: Molly Cox
text: DO NOT get the peppermint mocha here. I ordered it cold, it came out hot. They said I ordered a hot drink but I have NEVER in my life ordered a hot drink, I only drink cold so that was wrong on their part. My coffee didn't have the shot of espresso I paid for and the drink made me sick for 5 hours after drinking it. Idk if they tried to poison me or what out of retaliation of having to make another drink. :( I work right across the street so I was so excited but now I'm incredibly sad and disappointed.

name: Little Micchelle
text: When this Dunkin first opened I was extremely excited. Its right across from my job and it was a welcome addition to the area. But in the 3 times i've ordered from there every time it has been a struggle to get a simple powdered donut. I have eaten at Dunkins in many states. My family and I have driven 60 miles to get a dozen donuts from a Dunkin we know to be a good one. Today the lady at the window said I couldn't get a powdered donut because they are seasonal! What season is a powdered donut for? I was planning on frequenting this establishment but if i'm going to be outright lied to and denied items I know should be available I would rather drive across town to the krispy kreme.

name: Lil Yung Powerful
text: The employees have an attitude and the girl who started working in the beginning with the tattoos that has the morning shift is really slow...I was excited when they first open but oh boy was I wrong...Also it seems like they didn’t get no training.

text:
Cake Designs makes the most AMAZING cakes!
I have been ordering all of our family birthday cakes from Cake Designs for over 15 years and my experience has been terrific every single time.
Whatever theme or design I have asked for, Cake Designs has always come through with a gorgeous cake. The cake artists at Cake Designs are true artists. The cakes they create are absolutely beautiful works of art. At every birthday party, people always ask where the cake came from, because it's always outstanding!
And the Cake Designs cakes are scrumptious. They are so moist and light that we always order a cake that is way too big for the number of people we plan to serve, just so we can keep eating the yummy Cake Designs cake for days to come!!!!
The staff at Cake Designs is friendly, helpful and efficient. The cakes we have ordered have always been ready exactly when we asked for them to be ready. And Cake Designs is such a clean environment. They have albums and albums of photos of cakes they have made for every occasion imaginable. It's fun just to flip through the albums to see the gorgeous cakes they've made in the past - it's great inspiration for your current cake order.
Cake Designs is amazing and I highly recommend them for your cake needs!

name: Kristi Tahada
text:
The first thing that struck me when I walked in were all the ingredients. You could immediately tell that real cooking goes on here!

All the food my friend and I ordered was vegan and it was all amazing. She had the stir fry, turmeric tea, and the mushroom/ cheese turnover. I had the pina colada, the raspberry cake, and the chicken salad wrap. When I say everything was delicious... omg! The cake was an absolute revelation. I shared some with my friend and she said it reminded her of something happy from childhood.

While I loved the taste of the pina colada, I wasn't crazy about the texture. The bits of coconut and fruit chunks didn't do it for me though I am convinced that they use the real stuff since the pineapple affected my tastebuds just like real pineapple will do.

The display cases were sparse, as one reviewer noted, but I really appreciate placing an ethic of food conservation over aesthetics. There's no need for good food to go to waste, as it does every day in larger establishments, just to keep a display case full all the time. I was VERY happy with my meal as well as the service and will definitely be going back again soon for more! #veganlife

name: Shannon Campbell

I wasn’t really sure I was saying what I wanted quite right, but when I picked up the cake it was exactly what I pictured in my mind and was a huge hit. Everyone loved the way it looked and tasted. We ate it over a few days and even a couple of days after it was cut, it still tasted good and fresh. I am now responsible for all the future birthday party cakes for our group as we will not be using any other bakery.

name: Sasha Irby
text:
This place deserves WAY more recognition than they have. I seriously cannot believe my mouth. As a vegan, DO YOU KNOW how HARD it is to find even an ACCEPTABLE vegan cheese to make a good soul food worthy mac and cheese?! After trying this "cheese", I actually had to sit down and ask myself, "What else can I put this cheese on?" Hands down the best cheese I've ever had on my vegan journey. Nothing in the stores come close. Son't even get me started on the desserts. And now I found out they sell food too?!

Im just a stranger on the internet and there is no good reason why you should trust me, but when has that ever stopped you from making a bad decision before? Look, just go buy their cheese, their desserts, their food, JUST GET IT!! This is unacceptable how little recognition this place gets. Thank you to the owners for making QUALITY vegan food that I would not be ashamed to have my friends sample. 🙏🏾 I hope your business takes off even more than it already has. You deserve it!

resp.text: Thank you so much Sasha. It is a pleasure doing business with you and looking forward to many more visits.

text: This place is really good. The desserts are amazing but the food is just as good! I've had the egg spinach and feta croissant that was surprisingly great! I've also had the breakfast wrap which by itself was really good but the pesto sauce that comes with it was delicious and a perfect pairing to the wrap. I'd never heard of a fried peanut butter and jelly sandwich before so I had to try it and it was delish!  I highly recommend this place if you have a sweet tooth or want a really good breakfast! You can get it delivered.

We will definitely be coming by frequently, will be looking forward to try your cream puffs and cheese cake and fresh loaf next time.

name: Jiminy Cricket
text: I called to make an appointment for a small wedding cake and the lady said I could come any time. When I got there, they were too busy and asked if I could come back later which I did. When I came back at the agreed time, the lady spent about 5 minutes talking to me but could not provide a price list, serving list, or flavor list. When it was obvious to her that I had too many questions, she passed me off on her daughter claiming that she had to decorate a cake--I don't believe this because it was only 30 minutes until closing on a Saturday and they aren't open Sun/Mon. So then we had to start the conversation all over again with the daughter who promised to email me flavor and serving lists.  These never came arrived however, so we bought 2 beautiful and delicious cakes from the City Cafe nearby for a lot less money and trouble.

resp.text: So Sorry you had a bad experience. Yes I did have to decorate a cake. They had come in to get cake earlier that day and I had to put them off because we were so busy that day. I did have to go and finish the cake before closing. I am sorry we did mess up in not sending the list of cake flavors, But we did tell you we could make any flavor that you wanted as we do make all our cakes from scratch. I am glad to hear you found the cakes you wanted, as you were very undecided in what you wanted for a cake. So not sure it would have been more or less as we couldn't give you a price when you were so undecided about what design you wanted and most of the cake you showed us were Very fancy fondant which is a lot more than than a buttercream cake. Also you wanted the cake in less than two weeks, which is not traditionally enough time to order a wedding cake. You had emailed me on Thursday and ask if you could come in Tomorrow for a consult. And Friday we are not as busy as we are on Saturdays. Again I am sorry we were so busy when you came in to discuss the wedding cake

text: I was a bit disappointed.  Minimal selection of single items to buy and the shelves of baked items nearly empty.  The pieces of cake looked like they were haphazardly put into containers.  The front of the store was not well kept.

resp.text: I am so sorry, The previous owners only did cake orders. So we are trying to build up enough walk in clients to be able to stock the shelves fully. However if we do that as of now, a lot of it goes to waste and is to much profit loss. We do offer on the spot items such as Breakfast Burrito's, Fruit smoothies, Chicken Salad which can go on a croissant, wrap or sandwich.  We have Grilled Cheese or Omelets and those are not on display but made fresh to order, Also the cupcakes are iced on the spot rather than put in the case to dry out. We do usually have a large selection of cookies to choose from(all made from scratch), but we were bought out a couple of times this week and today we did not have a chance to make more.  IF you call ahead we can make whatever you are wanting. We also offer many Vegan Items, But again we really need a heads up on that so we can make if fresh for you, Unless it is the Vegan Burrito, grilled cheese etc which we can make on the spot.  Another thing is we are closed on Sunday and Monday so we do let supply run down on Friday and Saturday. Again I am so sorry for your disappointment. Please give us a call if there is something in particular you would like and we will do our best not to disappoint again.

Brittni

name: Bill Crawford
text:
My wife heard about The Flour Sack from her PT(knee surgery last week). Me trying to be a good husband, she told me that she would like to try so I immediately told her let's do it. We called to make our order and were both very happy with the customer service and ease of the process and selection on short notice. We were on the circle across town so we made it there in just a few minutes. I went inside and was greeted in the most cozy, comfy place I had ever been in Dothan by a very sweet, kind lady(wish I had gotten her name so I could thank her on here but too late now, thank you for you're awesome service). Our order was already prepared that quickly but the case had items my wife didn't mention so risking getting in trouble (lol not really but husband's will understand) I asked if I could add a few items and without hesitation she was ready to help me. She packaged it up, gave me a total, I paid, and left it was a wonderful all around experience. This was the simplest part of this review lol. Skip forward a few hours, we are home and have had dinner and my wife is ready to try out the cupcakes. We both had a red velvet cupcake first and we had to stop what we were doing and thinking about to take in the experience that was happening. I can not explain in words how perfect they were, texture, smell and the taste... OMG, hands down the best red velvet anything that I've ever had my entire life (I'm 33), we then had to try another one so we each tried a different one so we could taste more without eating too much and still try more because we are still both in shock of the amazing thing happening. I got a key lime cupcake and she got a birthday cake cupcake, again we both were blown away by how incredible this all was. She is actually rushing me now because I had to stop then and write this review to let anyone know, who has a sweet tooth or any reason to get a treat, this is the place to go. We will go back in future and tell everyone we know to go try it because it is that great of an all around experience start to finish. Thank you so much and we look forward to the next time.

Update to the review, this is the next day and my wife has started negotiating terms of the last cupcake because they are that amazing.

text: Dangerous!! Update, and response to owner***The coffee shop has closed down, but instead of notifying Google, and thanking their patrons by adding a notification to the phone number, they surrounded the property with dangerous dogs. They are VERY AGGRESSIVE! Please do not try to park in the lot or you might be bitten. If they don't rectify this situation I foresee a lawsuit in the near future. Update:  The closed sign can NOT be seen over the truck parked in the lot if you are pulling in from the double springs side. Regardless. Most people are looking for parking not for a closed sign before pulling in. I'd like to know how many places of business you go to that you circle looking for closed signs before heading to the parking lot. Google says you were open. You can update that, and you have the responsibility to. My young daughter was almost bitten by your dangerous dogs. Unfortunately, you won't have my business again. It is not acceptable to claim you are trying to protect patrons by getting them bitten by your dogs. If you can't update review sites with proper information, then your patrons will. Put up a barrier across the lot if you want to ensure people don't enter. You're not trying to keep out invaders. You're trying to protect future patrons. Act like it.

resp.text: The Coffee House is currently under renovations and is closed - Temporarily. Please abide by our prominently displayed CLOSED sign. There are many construction projects currently ongoing and we are not open to the public to ensure their safety.

text: Latte with a refill on black coffee for $3.85 in a very comfy little spot.

name: Shelia Dersham
text: Great place to meet

name: Shelia Dersham
text: Great place

name: Brye Lehmann
text: Cool place and friendly staff

name: Samantha Shu
text: Very easy transaction! Called and placed an order for my daughters bday cake! The woman on the phone was very nice and asked all the questions necessary! I told her what I wanted and they delivered! Better than I expected!

name: Olivia Williams
text: I am from out of town and wanted to surprise my friend on her birthday with some delicious cupcakes. I have passed the cute Little Cake Shop while visiting and decided to call to see if they could help me even though it was last minute. Lacy is who spoke with and she was amazing. She boxed me up a dozen of their fresh cupcakes, I paid over the phone, and my friend will be able to stop by and pick up her surprise. I am so happy with the wonderful customer service I received.

name: Jackie Emmett
text: Finally know where to get amazing cake! Absolutely delicious . I bought a couple cupcakes and they’re the best I’ve ever had !!

name: Marquisha Khamis

text: Bought pastries for $30 , got home, dry and tasteless, for a shop called little cake shop, not 1 cake able to buy in store

name: Marge D
text: So cute and delicous and the people who own and work there are so sweet and kind!!

name: Sharon Condon
text: Mexican wedding cookies didn't disappoint. Super service when personalizing cake artwork.

name: Kasie Braswell
text: Called in with less than 24 hrs notice and they did an amazing job! Cake was beyond our expectations and tasted delicious. My son wanted a pirates treasure chest and that’s exactly what he got!

name: meyber santos
text:
My experience was absolutely great. I order the cake over the phone and email what I wanted and they made exactly how I wanted...

All of our guests love the tasting cake😋

name: Kim Goodson
text: Awesome!!!!! The cake was beautiful and delicious ...the owner was extremely nice and can't wait til they are opened back up for customers to come in an view the tasty goodies !!!

name: Cindy Ross
text: The absolute worst experience. Ordered a cake for my brother’s surprise 50th Party. The Little Cake Shop was referred to me so I made an hour drive to pick up the cake a day before the party. The cake was ordered 8 weeks prior, pics were sent of the exact cake they made. I arrived and the cake looked nothing like the pictures.  When I explained I wasn’t happy they attempted to fix some of it after pulling up the picture I sent and it still looked botched. This cake was $90 and I explained I drove an hour and I wanted to be refunded. The heavy set girl behind counter explains to me in a very loud screaming voice they have been in business for 23 years and it was a family business. I received my money back but after this horrible experience I don’t have a cake for my brothers special day tomorrow. I would not recommend this business to my worst enemy.

name: Andrew Howard
text: Cake was wonderful!  Saved the day!  Birthday boy loved his cake!  The staff was very friendly and helpful.  Will certainly come back!

name: Anna Richardson
text: Every single time I order a cake it is pure perfection.  I will not get my cakes from anywhere else.

name: monica taggart
text: Great place to get cake

name: David Impastato
text: Great cakes for a great price.

name: Jessica Solis
text: They were sweet as was the cake !!

name: James McNaughton
text: Love their pastries. Apricot cheesecake my favorite. They also make specialty cakes. Ordered our wedding cake from here and it received many compliments from our guests.

name: Ethan Lewis
text: The best discovery! My mother and I were passing through and HAD to stop at this cute little bakery. They had many assortments of bite sized cheesecakes and tarts as well as the best Mexican wedding cookie you will ever put in your mouth. I can't wait to stop by again!

name: Niki Nichols
text: These ladies were so accommodating to my random last minute request! They got us exactly what we needed. I was so thankful as I had called a few other shops with no luck!

name: Nunya
text: I tried the Little Cake Shop and it just wasn't what I expected. I tried the vanilla cupcakes and the icing has a great texture but no taste. The cake itself was spongy and I like moist better. I wanted to try this place cause I have heard good things but they just didn't live up to my expectations. They are very nice though!!

name: Mobile Botanical Gardens
text: The talented folks at The Little Cake Shop created the most beautiful sheet cake for our special event — and it tasted incredible! They also prepared custom cookies that were melt-in-your-mouth yummy. Wonderful experience - as always - with these super talented bakers and artists.

name: E. Hilliard
text: Lovely people!! Lovely treats!!! Absolutely amazing customer service and the cakes are even better! Highly recommend!

name: Dr. Lindsay Greenlee
text: Excellent!  The ladies did a wonderful job with my wedding cake - it was gorgeous and tasted great!  Despite my minimal description of what I wanted, they managed to make a cake matching my exact vision. Also one of the few cake shops I found that would make a red velvet wedding cake. Highly recommended.

name: Sharon Anderson
text: The Little Cake Shop made the cake for a bridal shower that I co-hosted.  The cake was beautiful and the taste was heavenly! Everyone wanted to know where we had gotten it.  The cake was actually moist. Most cakes from bakeries seem dry and heavy to me....not this one.  The icing was perfect.  I usually have to scrape the icing off before eating cake.  This was sweet, but did not pucker anyone's face by being too sweet.  They worked with my budget and still turned out a beautiful and delicious cake.   Thank you Little Cake Shop.

name: Jim Unger
text: They made me a beautiful 100% Vegan birthday cake today and it tasted amazing!

name: Tara Beck
text: Last minute birthday cake for my son. They were amazing and worked with me to get every detail right. Will definitely use again.

name: Blair Ellenburg
text: We ordered a cake for Gwen's birthday and they did an amazing job! I explained what I was thinking and they took my idea and created the perfect cake! It was beautiful and tasted amazing. You definitely have to check them out!

name: Jade Hebert
text: Highly recommend NOT using them. When I had MULTIPLE discrepancies with my order they did not want to correct it and due to them not being open on the weekend I was stuck in my  dilemma. I did NOT have cream filled cupcakes (AS ORDERED) and they claimed my cake was made with cream cheese but me and ALL of my guest tasted buttercream! I brought a piece in and they tasted it. She said ‘well, it’s made with a buttercream base and we add cream cheese...’ THATS NOT WHAT I ASKED FOR! I was refunded a lousy $20! Very disappointed

name: Deborah Fulgham
text:
Worst experience with a place of business.
The cakes came out nothing like the photos I gave them to copy, not even close. The color was horribly wrong and I was embarrassed to display them at our party. People were shocked to find out that they were made by a "Professional" baker. Not only were they ugly but they were dry and my guest threw more cake away that they ate. When I called with my concerns I assumed since I was a repeat customer that would be willing to right their wrong. I asked for nothing but hoped they would offer something to make it right. They made excuses then hung up on me and ignored my next three calls. I will advise everyone I know to spend their hard earned money elsewhere. They care nothing for repeat customers. This was my 4th and final purchase.

name: Tracey Grimes
text: Highly recommended. They are very nice and professional company. They have beautiful cakes. My bother was planning his wedding when he was killed in a car wreck... one call to them and they didnt hesitate to work with us on the refund of the total prepaid cakes. Thank yall very much!

name: Dawn Miller
text: I stopped by and tried the chocolate cupcake with white icing and it was delicious! Ordered my daughters cake as soon as I was done..yeah it was that good!

name: Victoria Redmond
text: This place is great!! A hot spot for locals and gaining a name in surrounding states!! Service was great, and the cake, even better! Beautifully executed and very tasty!!! Definitely would recommend to all my family and friends!

name: Eddie Etheredge
text: Beautiful cake in Mardi Gras design, extremely friendly people, but quiet honestly poor poor flavor. Lots of compliments on its apoearance, but lots and lots of plates with two bites out of the slice then thrown in trash. Spend 200.00 on a cake you expect it to taste good, or at least I did. But it was pretty!

name: Charlene Price
text: Amazing cakes!!! not only in decorations but taste great too! so fresh. Thank you ladies.

name: Debra Stringer
text: The staff at ADT out of Pensacola enjoyed the little pastries. Very, very tasty.  Great job.

name: Teri Horne
text: I had a birthday cake with a paint party theme made at this shop for my grandson's 4th birthday.  They did an unbelievable job!  Everyone was taking pictures of it at the party.

name: Jessica Solis
text: They were sweet as was the cake !!

name: Griffin Shreves
text: The best place for cakes and more.

name: David Impastato

name: crystal cox
text: I have trusted The Little Cake Shop for multiple occasions and have ALWAYS been very pleased with their work!!

name: Victoria Redmond
text: Local favorite and hotspot! AMAZING cakes and even better people who work behind the scenes to make those amazing cakes!

name: Gloria Dennington
text: Great service and the people are the greatest

name: Nicholas Roussos
text: Great cakes and great service! If you can dream, they can bake it.

name: skiebluedragon
text:
Pricy and poor customer service.
It seemed like it was a hassle to fill our order of tarts and cookies.

name: Barbara Byrd
text: Assorted cakes and cookies

name: Faith McMillan
text: Doesn't answer phone calls. Their number has a busy signal the past 4 days. I just moved to the area and can't find a bakery (locally) to make my child's birthday cake. This business really needs to post a valid phone number or plug their phone in. Thumbs down.

name: An G
text: They have one of the better tasting strawberry cupcakes I've ever had. Icing had strawberry juice that made it taste better and the cupcake had fruit bits in them. We also tried the wedding cake cupcake (basic white cake that was very moist, vanilla icing was good), the carrot cupcake (quite good) and the vanilla cupcake with chocolate icing (chocolate was delicious). Overall, the cupcakes were all moist, very tasty but had slightly too much icing vs cupcake. The takeaway box had VERY little to be desired. No self respecting cupcake shop should have a box that doesn't have cupcake holders in them. All the cakes stuck together. 5 stars if it weren't for the box.

name: Tim Lynch
text: Was driving by and my 5 year old convinced me he and his sister deserved a cupcake after seeing the sign "Best Cupcakes". So happy we stopped in. Delicious. Quality pastries.  I'm a brownie guy, and the butterscotch brownie was top quality.  You can tell it scratch made!

name: Chris Bartz
text: 100% recommend! I ordered cupcakes for a bridal shower: strawberry with cream cheese icing and traditional wedding cake. Both were delicious! Not only did they taste great, they looked amazing. The cake was moist and flavorful and the icing was yummmmmmy. Everyone loved them. The staff is so nice and accommodating. Do yourself a favor and give this bakery a try!

name: Melissa Bowles
text: The cupcakes are AMAZING. I think I’ve tried every flavor and loved them all!. The cookies are also yummy, especially the chocolate chip. The owner and staff are wonderful and very accommodating. If you haven’t tried this bakery yet you’re definitely missing out!

name: Shelia Kennedy
text: first if all, when i called the bakery, the lady who answered was rude. But i still wanted delicious bakery cupcakes, so i placed my order anyway. I called ahead of time to order BIRTHDAY cupcakes. I was told I would have 6 birthday cupcakes (as I ordered). This was the day before Halloween, which was why i called to make sure I could get birthday cupcakes. When i arrived, i was given a box of 6 HALLOWEEN cupcakes. I dtated that i wanted birthday sprinkles and was then told "well, its halloween tomorrow so were only making Halloween cupcakes". I was disappointed because i had ordered ahead and was told it would be no problem. Then i was asked if i wanted to leave a tip. Which i did, reluctently (but thats on me). So paid over $20 for cupcakes, plus a $3 tip. It was not what i ordered and honestly, the yellow cupcakes were good but the chocolate ones were not, they were dry and seemed to be old. I had been there before and received great service and delicious cupcakes but this time, was very disappointed. Overpriced, rude service, and did not get what i ordered at all.

name: leigh taylor
text: The cupcakes are delicious!

name: Rhonda Clark-Ross
text:
Thank you so much for making our gender reveal special... Your cupcakes were delicious and I appreciate you taking care of my special order on such short notice. Awesome staff, friendly and personable. Highly recommend.

Rhonda R.

name: Lene Legrone
text:
If you haven’t tried this bake shop, you are missing out. She made the most amazing Game Of Thrones cake & It looked just like the picture. Renee and her staff are very talented can’t thank you enough! One more thing
Usually when a cake looks so amazing, The cake is dry. NOT this one. It was so moist and delicious.
I don’t know how they do it.
But the next time you want a phenomenal cake that will blow your guest away, try this bake shop. You will not be disappointed!

name: ry godwin
text: It was amazing!!!! Would recommend for anyone looking for a delicious treat!!!

name: Lorraine Muscarella
text: I had a birthday cake from there and it was terrible.  The cake was soggy where the filling was.  The cake itself didn’t taste right, like it had been frozen and thawed out.  It was decorated more like a wedding cake than a birthday cake. The icing was disgusting and the cake made 3 people sick.  Would not recommend or go back to this shop.

name: Debra Morrow
text: The ownership has changed as of September 2017.  The bakery products are no longer excellent. They are not even good -- They are tolerable if one is desperate for something sweet.  I bought five items expecting the same deliciousness from the previous owner.  The products were dry and lacked quality ingredients.  Because I was expecting the same quality products, I did not look closely at what I was buying.  Had I looked closer, I would have seen that they were different.  They did not look good either.  From the previous owner, I had bought many cookies, bars, cakes, slices of cake, and cupcakes for family, friends, students, co-workers, and myself.  Every time and everything was above board.  I shall not ever visit this shop again, unless the previous owner returns.

name: Timothy Jenkins
text: My wife and I had the opportunity to try the gluten free cupcakes from Something Sweet Bake Shop.  While my wife's diet is restricted, mine is not.  These cupcakes were so delicious that I could not tell that they were gluten free.  If you are in need of gluten free cakes or cupcakes, give Renee a chance to amaze you with her recipe.

name: Josh Null (Gulf Coast Finc. Advisors)
text: Some of the best desserts I've ever had. Great friendly service! Highly recommend!

name: Gail Okelley
text:
I thought I would try these cupcakes since the sign said they are the best cupcakes in Alabama. I must say I was very disappointed after paying over $8 for 3 cupcakes. There was nothing special about them and very over priced. My son took one bite and threw the rest away. What a waste of $8.

Very disappointed

name: Matt Gallagher
text: Im visiting from Boston and bought a carrot cake cup cake it was the best cupcake I've ever had in my life. A great experience inside the shop too. 5 stars all around

name: Eva Klemann
text: My customers loved  the cakes I purchased for them at Christmas. Everyone including myself are huge fans. There is nothing in this area that compares. Try the Red Velvet!

name: Nunya
text: Vanilla cupcakes here are the greatest. The icing she uses is awesome!! It's not to sweet but Heaven with a hint of almond!!! Great Oreo cake and Lemon Bars!! I just moved to Daphne and saw this place from the restaurant across the street and decided to try her cupcakes and they are Heaven!!

Wow!  The Lemon Bars Are Epic !!!

These ladies are crafting the finest desserts I have ever tasted.

Thank you for the joy you bring to my house.

Alan Hudson

name: Samuel Cooley
text: Hands down one of my favorite shops in Trussville. The food is amazing. I wish you the best of luck. :)

resp.text: Thank you so much Mr Cooley for the kind words and Great review.

name: Joe Duncan
text: Been buying from Lee for a while. Everything is excellent. Really like the blueberry beagles and the challah bread. The cinnamon rolls are great.

resp.text: Thank you so much Mr Duncan for great review

name: Kathy Hood
text: Everything I have tried is wonderful. My favorites are the jalapeño cheddar bread and the peanut butter cookies. You will not be disappointed.

resp.text: Thank you very much. So glad you enjoyed them. Peanut butter cookies are my favorite too. Come back to see us real soon.

name: Wayne Jordan
text: Amazing quality and service! We bought Breads and cookie’s and we WILL be back for more. If you are in the area, this is a must try.

resp.text:
Thank you so much, I am so Happy y'all like them. Look forward to serving y'all and everyone else.
Lee

text: Love It, Love It !!!  Get one of everything. :)

name: XPLOSION 2
text: Ordered a cookie cake a week ahead and actually had to change when it was ready due to work not letting me off even though o requested well ahead of time. Once they found it they had no problem changing it. I think the lady I spoke to on the phone was Jessica and she was just lovely and so polite.

resp.text: XPLOSION, thank you for the 5 star review! We really appreciate you! 😊

name: Sharon Cater
text: When I picked up my cookie cake that I ordered on line to make sure the spelling was correct, the fisrt thing I noticed was my last name was spelt wrong. My name is Cater not Carter.  The young lady at the counter asked someone to fix it. After a while, the agreement was made that the name was not as ordered.  When showed to me this time, I saw that an exclamation point had been put after Cater instead of a comma. The young lady said,  "You want that fixed too?" I  said no and left because I was detecting negativity. When I looked at the cake at home, I see that my daughter's first name was also spelt wrong.  The cake had Shavome instead  of Shavonne.  I called the store to speak with a manager.  I was informed that the manager was gone. I had to ask several times when he would be in before I was told the next day.  I  do hope I get to speak with a manager when I call back. I will repost then.

name: Michael Sims
text:
I coordinated a custom cookie a week ago.  When I texted this morning, they said they didn't have enough time and they would have to make something else instead.  I was unhappy, but, what can you do?

When we got there to pick it up, they pulled through and got it done.  They made it happen and pictures of the cookie have circulated among the friends and gotten many compliments.  Thanks, Great American Cookie Company.

resp.text: Hi Michael! Thank you so much for your business. We're happy to hear everything turned out great with your order.

name: Madison Deal
text: I would honestly give no stars. They didn’t have sugar cookies or any coke. They told me this after I waited five minutes on them doing whatever to come over and finally be rude. Go to  a different shop.

resp.text: Madison, we are so sad to hear that you didn't have a great experience! Please know that we have informed the franchise owner due to the fact that each location is independently owned!

name: Molly Shelton
text: They went above and beyond to make my son's wishes come true for a mario and luigi birthday cake! It looks amazing and did a great job! Thank you all i have one happy 6 year old boy!

name: Denice Carter
text: Called to order a cookie cake. Was told they were too busy and to call back. Called back and got a fax sound every time.  I realize there are busy times but there should be someone there to make sure all orders are taken care of.

resp.text: Hi Denice, we're sorry to hear about your experience with our store. Customer service is one of our top priorities. We will look into this issue more to make sure it is handled better in the future. Please give us a chance to correct the situation.

name: Sheila Patterson
text: Bridgestreet had very good fresh cookies.   Beautifully decorated frosted cookies and super nice ladies working.  They were very busy.

name: Lynne Brooks
text: Ordered a cake for my best friend a Dr. They made a fantastic cookie cake for her.With a medical theme.

name: Patrick Springer
text: Great cookies.

name: Jeannabeanna Stephens
text: A little expensive.

name: David Rawlins
text: Wanted a design they didn't have but agreed to try. They nailed it!!!

name: Butch Cassidy (Flying Bryan)
text:
Good prices on most items I buy. Selection was great and the produce was very good.  They also have a good selection of local craft beers.
I'm sorry I don't live closer or I would shop here more often.
Clerks were very helpful and pleasant to deal with.

name: Beverly Nelson
text:
I had the Baker that was to Bake my 59th Bday Cake cancel due to unforseen reasons at the last minute. It was too late to order a Bday Cake like I wanted it. So, I went in to the Bakery here and requested (3) 8" round vanilla layers. It was professionally put in a nice carrier for me. ($19.99)
I stopped in their Florist area & bought some beautiful Flowers for $2.00
I came home & did the Decorating myself & here are the pictures on my own Cake Stand....it was delicious!!

name: Phillip Forsyth
text: Excellent selection on pretty much every grocery item we need! We frequent this location a couple of times a week. Great weekly deals on meats and fresh produce. My better half never misses a chance to drop by the bakery section to see if the gourmet cookies are buy one, get one free, which they often are. There is also a great variety of wines and imported beers right by the deli in the back. We love our Winn Dixie and the cashiers are always friendly and helpful.

name: Oscar Mcclenton
text:
Okay so this review is a bit unique, because over all it was an enjoyable experience. I came in with A LOT OF COINS, to cash in with the coin star machine. Mostly pennies, over 10,000 of them actually haha. And the employee (not specifying gender as I don't want to misuse pronouns on someone that I have no clue on their choice of gender or lack thereof) was so kind, patient and professional. Thank you!

Now the not so good, there was an employee that was working the closest register to the coinstar that the other employee refered me to go cash in my coinstar vouchers with, and the employee flatly, rudely, denied exchanging my vouchers, then making a face that one would only expect to see if the employee was changing a babies diaper for the first time and looked behind to the other employee at the second register stating "uuuughh I just don't wannnaaaa I don't liiiikeee ittttt" seriously? Alright, I'll go back to the nice one :) needless to say my vouchers were promptly cashed out and apologies were made, which was so nice, thank you employee at the customer service desk, you were awesome and made my experience Great. You need a raise and a promotion.

name: David Johnson
text: Love the crab legs there always fresh and good. The people are very nice and generous the crab legs are on sale with a winn dixie card for 11.99 until the sale goes off.

name: Christa Morphis
text: Very helpful people and they always have the best items. This Winn Dixie has the BEST selection of foods for those on a strict diet such as Keto, Whole30, gluten-free, Paleo, etc. Vegetables are always fresh and in stock!

name: Donna A
text: I visited my mom in Alabama for about 3 weeks. Winn-Dixie was the only place that I shopped for food. I liked it so much I actually put the app on my phone. I'm back up north. I took my Mom to live with me.. When I go back down there to pack up the rest of her house, I intend to shop at Winn-Dixie so I'm keeping the app on my phone.

name: Jason Masters
text: Their website is inaccessible for those with disabilities, and they chose to spend hundreds of thousands of dollars on legal fees rather than the thousand dollars it would have cost to make their website accessible like every other website on the internet. 1 star for a cruel and callous company.

name: Tomma Padgett
text: Nice clean store. Enjoy shopping there. They have some things you can't find other places and then they don't have other thing that I want or need. A little pricey but still a good place to shop.

name: Sonya Milam Rollins
text: I went in to use Western Union. The young lady was so helpful. I had always used money gram at other locations. The young lady took time to explain the difference. She was nice, patient, and very informative.

name: Sherita Smith Brasher
text: Love this store great selection and good prices

name: Dave Walker
text: There's a lady that work in the seafood section that's out of sight she is so helpful and friendly it just makes you want to 😄 smile all day

name: Suzan Webster
text: So clean and quick, friendly,helpful employees also Bakery has fresh baked bread been trying to get some for days Walmart had been out cuz there Evan wasn't functioning anymore or something anyway thanks Winn-Dixie

name: Sandrs Abbott
text: This mask thing is out of control. I wear mine religiously & wish everyone else would also comply, but they won’t. I had mine on while shopping & while checking out at self checkout today. I needed to ask if I was ringing up the .25 per lbs sweet potatoes, but the employee just plain could not understand me. She was about 15 feet from me & not another soul around us. I pulled my mask down to repeat my question after the 3rd attempt. Her only answer was for me to please put my mask on. I never/ever wanted to slip it down to begin with & I’m truly sorry she is hard of hearing & should be doing a job that her disability doesn’t prevent her from doing safely.  I had to leave, and left my shopping behind. Publix is so much nicer & more helpful.

name: Mrs “Melana114” White
text:
On multiple occasions they have not had sale items in stock, even on the first day of a sale.

Made the 60 mile trip to purchase  the whole tenderloin for $7.99 lb. The senior lady who works in the meat department was sarcastic and rude, definitely not in the correct line of work. Said they only had the $16.99 lb tenderloin but the other would be in stock the following morning. Refused our request to allow a substitution at a discount.

So, we make a SECOND 60 mile trip only to be told by another gentleman "oh, we haven't been able to order any".  How it goes from coming in today to never even being ordered is beyond me, but somebody isn't telling the truth. Then the same senior lady remarks, oh yall are the ones from yesterday. No apology for the inconvenience, nothing.

Asked for a manager and explain how we've now made two 60 mile trips. He just shrugs it off saying the ads were made 2 weeks ago and they just weren't able to get it in stock. I asked if we could at least get a raincheck or the $16.99 at a discount. NOPE. "In these times " they just can't predict blah blah blah.  I pointed out that in these times, a simple update to apps and websites would remove misleading sales they know they can't fulfill.

At the same time I was speaking to the manager, my husband was speaking to the butcher about just getting one of the 16.99 lb tenderloins and he says, oh they're all gone, we used them as substitutes for customers yesterday. (WOW. Must have been friends or family because they sure wouldn't do it for us!)

Poorly managed. Poor customer service. No longer worth the trip.

text:
The service has been much better than of late. The recent remodel was really nothing more than a few new display fixtures in the produce and bakery department and basically flipping the store around. It is much harder to locate products you bought on a regular basis. There is a certain individual that works in customer service that provides NO SERVICE. If asked about something she acts as if you are bothering her. Too many times I’ve had issues only to find out the manager on duty was not available. The fact that I enjoy interacting with the younger cashiers and the ones that stock and front the shelves is the only reason I continue to go back. Another large grocery store is only a few miles further and I’ve moved my larger purchases there and only buy small amount of food products to fill in if not available at the other store and I buy medication at Winn Dixie as the pharmacy staff is outstanding.

Two years ago I would give this store 5 stars but today it is hit or miss on quality service and leaning more towards miss most visits.

name: Mark Barber
text:
I was really excited about this place being under new ownership. But I just paid for a burnt cookie from a store that specializes in cookies.. :(

In terms of what you would normally pay for a cookie, it was certainly not a cheap one to be burnt.

resp.text: I sincerely apologize for your experience at mylksI also would like to apologize for getting back to you so late  I would like you to give us another chance so if you come by I will give you a half a dozen free cookies for your inconvenience sincerely Robyn the new owner

name: Nikita Hoffman
text: Enjoyed Mylks Cookies for the first time today. They're open! Delicious!! They have made to order giant ice cream sandwiches, nutella filled cookies (delish!!), pb&j stuffed cookies, red velvet with filled buttercream and brookies (my fav, it's half cookie/half brownie)!! I was really impressed by the selection, kindness of the owner and variety to settle my sweet tooth. Will have to make a trip back to keep supporting this sweet, family-owned business!!

resp.text: Thank you so much for your kind words. Happy we were able to help you with your sweet tooth and you enjoyed your cookies I hope to see you the next time you visit to our Cookies Store.

name: Juan Cepero
text: Cookies were delicious and cookie dough was awesome. We were in the area for work and had a sweet tooth that needed satisfying. This place definitely came through and the staff was very friendly and patient as we were trying to decide what to get. Needless to say they made it very easy when they started bringing out fresh cookies from the back lol This place is a must try, One of my personal favs is the peanut butter and jelly cookie.

resp.text: Thank you so much for your kind words With your enjoyable experience with Our store and staff . We are so happy that you enjoyed your peanut butter and jelly cookie it a lot of peoples favorite.

name: Sandy Toomer
text: The cookies are the absolute best on the country!  Delivery can be ordered through Tiger Town To Go or you can have a pick up order called in advance, but remember you have to "pick them up".  My orders are always FRESH and DELICIOUS.  The owner bakes fresh cookies every morning, from scratch.  They also have  sandwich cookies that are incredible.  Cookie Cakes, single layer and their specialty 6 LAYER Cookie Cake.

name: Cathy Lott
text: Sweetest employee and ever so patient with my grandkids age 2 and 7

resp.text: It was our pleasure to serve you and your family. We are family owned business and treat a our customers like family.  We are excited for your next visit.

name: SueAnne Griffith
text: Consistently awesome cookies.

name: Leisa Coleman
text: The cookies are delicious, but the customer service needs work. After informing the owner that it was my first time visiting, she didn't care to offer suggestions or help me figure out the best pricing structure (I was ordering for my office). After selling 12 cookies for $30, you'd think she'd crack a smile!

name: Collins Monette
text: walked into the place getting a gift and when the lady working started to put them into a bag i nicely asked if she could wrap them into a box if it wasn’t too much trouble. this was a huge mistake. she then continued to throw cookies into the box showing me that she had an attitude. the cookies are just eh and the tatted up woman working should be fired. i won’t be back

resp.text: Hi there . Sorry about you previous experiance. Mylks is under new ownership as of May 2019. Would love you to come back and try again... We have some new cookies, eatable cookie dough (new) and cookie cakes. Thanks...

resp.text:
Thank you we can ship our to any state but
Alaska or Hawaii

name: Haley
text: Mylks has some of the best cookies in Auburn. BUT customer service is severely lacking. Do not come in to Mylks with high customer service expectations, but know the poor service experience is worth a delicious treat.

name: Marlene Powell
text: Quick and friendly service.

name: Haiden Boyles
text: These cookies are awesome but I work in the service industry and I have to say the lady who works here is one of the reasons I will not go back. I've never been made to feel like I was not wanted in a business more in my life. I am a very easy going person with a pretty simple cookie order. It just seemed like putting a cookie in a bag was too much to not do with a bad attitude.

name: Rebecca L
text: My husband and I stop by Mylks a couple times a month for a cookie fix. He loves the caramel filled snickerdoodles and I love the chocolate chip cookie sandwich. They are consistent and always delicious. This is definitely one of my favorite places to go when I have a sweet tooth.

name: Michael Holland
text: Cookies are good and all, but dear lord. The owner is an absolute beast to deal with. When you come in the most she might say is "what do you want" and that's it. If I say "thank you" or "good morning" or "how are you today", all I get back in return is a glare akin to a mad alley cat. No clue what her deal is on a personal level. She just seems to hate her customers.

name: Emma King
text: The girl working the front with all the tattoos was SOO RUDE!! I was trying to get her opinion on the cookies and all she would answer was yes or no. The display in the fridge was very unorganized therefore I bought something I do not like! Instead of letting me exchange it for something I do like, they simply said no! My friend also had a hair in her cookie

name: Candice Osborne
text: New management - finally! Awesome cookies with a friendly, upbeat atmosphere! You have to stop!!

name: Andrew Cartner
text: Excellent food. However I like to think I am very easy to please but service was borderline aggressive. My trip was a while ago now so the service staff could be different now but be prepared in case.

name: Heather Henderson
text: The cookies are good enough but the customer service is downright bad. My husband and I  have brought our son here a handful of times and every single time the same woman is so off-putting. She isn't aggressively rude, she just makes you feel so uncomfortable that you want to leave. No greeting, no smile, no customer service at all. Working with the public isn't for everyone and there's nothing wrong with that but hire someone who can do that for you because clearly your reviews have taken quite a hit because of it. Nothing against her personally, I don't know her enough to insult her but, we definitely won't be back because of her specifically. We just felt too uncomfortable.

text: The cookies are delicious, but the service is pathetic. I spent $50+ on 24 cookies and the least I expect is a "thank you" or a  "you're welcome" from the staff. Instead, I got nothing in response. Not a word or an acknowledgement of appreciation for my business. It also wouldn't hurt if the staff came to work dressed in something besides their pajamas. Tons of room for improvement in the customer service department.

text: I ordered a huge batch of cookies and rice krispy treats for an event and they encouraged a wonderful reaction from the students at the event! I was quite happy with the service and the taste and would definitely order from here again, especially since they allowed me to pick up my order before opening hours!!!

text: Friendly service, alright cookies. Nothing to go crazy about though. It's conveniently close to campus for a quick cookie fix.
