name: Chris Dinsmore
text: I won't be back! I own a taxi service so I deal with rude drunk people all the time but the lady that was working yesterday afternoon was prob the rudest person uv ever had to deal with!word of mouth goes a long way.u never know who is walking in your store or who he or she knows.this person needs to get out of dealing with the public asap she is going to run your customers away!

resp.text:
This is more a response to those reading this than to Mr. Dinsmore.  He is a rude man, who was never a customer, but a delivery driver. He took offense to my actions following a mix up with an order he was due to pick up.  Instead of acting like an adult, he acted childish  started sending angry emails to the "owner" of the shop.
He actions grew  increasingly unsettling, and eventually I had to request he not be sent to pick up delivery orders from Mylk's any more, as he made me feel unsafe.

name: David Hathcock
text: Best Snickerdoodles I've ever had! Try their ice cream sandwiches.

name: Grace Tatum
text: I absolutely love these cookies. The best ones around. The only other place around that I can go to get desserts this good is located all the way in Opelika and the hours suck. They are never overcoked, always consistent, and it doesn't matter what you get it will always be good! I've had a lot of cookies from a lot of different places and no one else can compare! They cost about $2 a piece, but they are big and delicious so I really think that's reasonable. A few of the reviews have referred to an employee that wasnt that nice(In my opinion she is just quiet). If they would have been more observant they would have noticed she has cuts all over her arms. Have some compassion people! I don't know her story and neither do they. And if you dont go buy cookies here it may shut down and if that happens you'll have to deal with people who are a lot meaner! People who can't get there cookie fix. I don't want to imagine that, its horrible!

Staff can be quite rude when this is pointed out so at this point I've just stopped ordering what I want and just grab whatever. Wish the manager could fix this but I rarely ever see him. Wish I could get my money back

text: Conveniently located (for students) in the LRC building. Nearly inaccessible for others. Can be busy at lunch, and at the top of every hour when classes change. Prices and taste are good, but not notable. Staff are nice,  even when the line of customers stretches out the door.

name: Christian Mays
text: It is what it is. Quick bagels and food that is convenient but nothing to write home about. Can't complain. Very fast and pretty cheap for a bagel.

name: Matthew Pearson
text:
If you're a UAB student, just go here.. Skip Panera and Starbucks if you're looking for food. The sandwiches here are SO MUCH better than Panera. I mean in another league. And they cost less.

I have yet to try their coffee, but as they seem to serve caribou coffee, I am sure it will be more than adequate. I will be skipping Starbucks except when I am in the mood for a frappuccino.

YES it is worth the walk(not really far from anything anyways). Even better if you live in Blazer or NFR.

It may not be the absolute best food out there, but for UAB students with dining dollars? Best I've had. That is unless you want a burger.

tl;dr Best food I've had at UAB unless you're craving for a burger, then go the Den.

text: There is something about a new Publix that makes you want to shop there. The meats, seafood, fruits and vegetables all looked good. I only purchased veggies and spicy wings this time. That is the Publix difference!

resp.text: Thanks for your kind feedback and for shopping with us, Bob! ¤Angel

name: Girli Green
text: This was possibly the worst shopping experience I have EVER had. The cashier and the gentleman that helped bag my groceries were pleasant. He was even friendly. My thoughts on every single other employee I encountered would require a long tirade of profanity. I will NEVER go back there. I can barely believe Publix would allow this crew to operate their store. Such a shame.

resp.text: Can you please reach out to our Customer Care line: 1-800-242-1227, or private message us on Facebook here: https://www.facebook.com/publix/, and we will be happy to help get this concern addressed with the Store Manager. ➳Cinthya

name: Winston Smith
text: Shopped at the Publix at the Morgan Road Plaza on 6/1/2021 at about 5:30pm. From the deli, we bought sushi and "Quick Shrimp Bites". While the sushi was really pretty good, the shrimp bites is why there is a "1 star" rating. My wife and I ate in the parking lot. The shrimp was cold as were the potato wedges. I really cannot understand how a brand new, flagship, Publix  serves cold shrimp and potatoes that were supposed to be hot.

resp.text: Can you please reach out to our Customer Care line: 1-800-242-1227, or private message us on Facebook here: https://www.facebook.com/publix/, and we will be happy to help get this concern addressed with the Store Manager. ➳Cinthya

resp.text: Thanks for the love and for shopping with us, Michael! ¤Angel

text: They need to make fresh tea more often. Their tea is often old and sour. I've gotten disgusting sour iced tea a couple times at this location.

text: America Runs on Dunkin. This place is beautiful. Great staff and I love Dunkin donuts. This is my new favorite place to get coffee.

text: Fast service and friendly workers. The drive through runs quickly, even on busy weekday mornings.

name: Rex Cardan
text: This is the best Dunkin Donuts in Birmingham. Clean, fast and friendly staff and consistent quality of drinks.

name: Melissa Needham
text: I hardly ever have an issue with the Vestavia location, but they need to work on their customer service. Especially when they are getting the orders wrong. They are there to make the coffee and make the orders right for the customers, so they shouldn't get mad at us when the order is wrong. Also when you hand a customer a drink you should hand them a straw to go with it and not get mad when they sit there and ask for a straw. Just some things to think about.

text: Went in to order some donuts and coffee. Ordered a lrg mocha frappe and lrg caramel frappe. Lady assumed i meant in the same drink. I didnt catch it till i received the one drink with both in it. I then had to purchase another one so atleast one would be correct which wasnt that big of a deal but she didnt offer to fix it.

text: I love Dunkin' Donuts. I used to be a Krispy Kreme fan but have been converted. Great donuts, great coffee, excellent service what more could you want?

text: This new place has a great atmosphere.  Very accommodating and patient team. Always fresh doughnuts  Food is good and they get my quick coffee fix right each time. Great place if your driving by.

text:
Very pleased to have this new location, ESPECIALLY because the staff is INCREDIBLE.
I'm also extremely thankful that they are continuing to adhere to the Covid-19 health guidelines, with everyone wearing masks and gloves, and touchless drive thru.

Thank you for holding steady at this location.

name: notthebeesxoxo
text:
This is the best DD in town. I love DD coffee but struggled for a while to find a DD that can consistently make a drink right. Every place, they either made it too strong, not strong enough, not sweet enough, too sweet... Just tons of issues and lots of wasted money on coffees I couldn't even force myself to finish.

Then they opened this location and they are the most consistent DD I've been to and I go here every single day during the week. The people are also so nice and the drive thru, even when busy, is so fast! There could be 7 cars in line and I'll still be done in 10 mins or less.

resp.text: Ms. Huffman- Thank you for your review.  As we discussed on the phone, we definitely made a mistake with your order.  Once we realized what had happened we were unfortunately out of the actual items you had ordered.  That particular day was very busy for us and we were running low on products. We do have a huge variety of flavors, but like a lot of bakeries we do bake fresh daily which means we can and occasionally do sell out of products.  If there is anything else that I can do other than what we discussed on the phone, please reach out to me at patrick@gigismontgomery.com.  Thanks!

I called and was told the manager was not available and wouldn't be back for a few days. I left a message, but was advised to call back.  I called back and there was still no manager available.  I left my name and number and asked for a return call.  Still no call.  I left a message on their facebook page and got no response there either.  I will not go back to the Montgomery location.

resp.text: Rachel- I'm terribly sorry our cupcakes made you sick, however this is the first we've heard of this. There have been no messages left for us in store nor a message on Facebook. name: Mae Shinigami
text: 2 stars for customer service & presentation.  The clerk was friendly & the cupcakes are indeed pretty. But 3 stars off for taste, quality, and price. First off the cake itself is either dry & flavorless, or dense & heavy like an undermixed muffin. The tower of frosting tries to hide that fact, & would've succeeded if it wasn't just a sickening pile of one-dimensional sugar. I've tried chocolate, yellow cake, red velvet & apple pie...ALL suffered from the same looks-better-than-it-tastes syndrome. Even if the frosting was redeemable, it takes up 75% of the cupcake, so you're being overcharged for whipped sugar! Finally, they charge you for a regular cupcake what other local (better) bakeries charge for a jumbo. If this is what a cupcake franchise is like no wonder the fad is dying fast...

I picked up one, then a other and then another peach only to find they were Green&Fuzzy...gave up on the peaches and showed them to the produce mgr who just shrugged his shoulders like he didnt care at all. So I went to buy a bag of tangerines. Guess what, when I picked up the bag all the ones on tbe bottom were Green & Fuzzy too. I went back to the mgr and he rolled his eyes and said "what do you want? I check everyday...it happens". That level of rot does Not happen over night and his attitude was the worse. Publix customers Pay More and I dont mind for better quality and service. After 14 yrs shopping at Publix for my Family of 4, I quit and found out that I get quality produce and other things at Piggly Wiggly for half the cost and great service. That's approx $600/month of my money Publix has lost. This particular Publix is not in as affluent an area as the one I used to shopping for 14 years but I would hate to think that the lack of $$ is why the products and service are inferior

Has one employee that will blatantly argue that you are wrong about what you  payed for an item as you are trying to show them on your receipt to prove to them "they" are wrong. text:
I was a big fan of this place when they were 24 hours. Now i prefer krogers. They open at 7 and close at ~8-10. Between the oblivious patrons blocking the path, the 'buy me' displays everywhere and the daytime stocking carts it's very frustrating just to move around in the store. There is no room. This isn't the employee's fault as employee's aren't displays or stocking carts. This is a managerial fault. Have daytime stocking or 'buy me' displays. Don't clutter the aisles with both. If I had to sum up my review it's just 'store very cluttered'.

I don't have the same frustrations moving around in other grocery stores. This is a walmart specific problem.

I was shopping last night and, out of the blue as is soooooo common with severe vertigo, I went into a panic attack and was almost in tears as I raced to the front of the store to check out and leave, and that sweet girl immediately noticed something was wrong.  I told her I was just trying to check out quickly because I was on the verge of a severe panic attack, and she raced around to me and put her arms around me and spoke the sweetest, kindest words, and I knew she was a gift straight from God!!  She checked me out and had me take a seat on the bench right up front and across from her checkout line, and just kept talking to me in between her other customers.  GIVE THAT GIRL A PROMOTION AND A RAISE!!

Sorry example of a wonderful cake.

resp.text: Hi Virginia!  All of our cakes are baked fresh and are very moist and our icing is true homemade icing and we use the best of ingredients. Just give us a call to let us know when you’d like it!  256-486-9471

name: Eileen Wargacki
text: Website said open on Tuesday at 730 am. Arrived at location, not open. 33 mile drive. Gave one star because I had to to give a rating. Will not return.

resp.text:
I am so Sorry that you drove out to the shop and it was closed! I have actually been closed since March 13th due to Covid and then the road closed and no one is traveling down to the businesses down our way. I have actually put in an complaint with Google because I have edited my hours to show “temporarily closed” and they keep changing me back to regular hours and this has been going on since May! I don’t know where you drove from
But I’d like to get you some pies to you to make up for coming that distance and us being closed...... that is what has kept us alive during all This and me not closing permanently is taking orders for pickup.

text: Today was my first time shopping at the Winn-Dixie and I can say everything is very cheap and I loved the sale they was having. I couldn’t beat the prices I paid for because the prices I would of paid for in the city I live in would have been higher. As far of today I will be shopping here from now for groceries, water, and laundry detergent etc, and snacks. The workers were very friendly and helpful. It was my first time using the digital coupons (app) to receive discounts and I already gained points. ❤️❤️❤️ I love this store already!!!!

name: Chris Hanes
text:
Winn Dixie is not exactly known for its cleanliness but this store ranks up there with any Publix or other fancy grocery store in terms of being clean, well-lit and staffed by friendly folks.

There is a Public right down the road but I often find myself here instead when visiting town as the prices are great and the staff is friendly. Sometimes during the later hours, things aren't quite as great, thus the 4 star review instead of a 5 star review.

Also, sometimes on Friday nights they have the smoker going out front and music is playing and it's a party at the local WD and it doesn't get much better than that.

name: Jason Yeager (Jason)
text: Good store to shop, but there have been too many times that I have visited and left without the items I went to get. It seems they have difficulty keeping stock of sale items. Deli food items are often gone before mid-afternoon so don't go searching for a fully cooked rack of ribs or rotisserie chicken for dinner after 1:00 or so. They also mislabel fish in the seafood market. I have seen them selling the lane snapper species labeled as the higher quality, better tasting and more expensive red snapper. This is a federal law violation so they might want to be careful what they call their fish. They usually have a decent selection of meats,  but they often have an attitude if something is not out there and you ask them to get you the item.

name: Tim Griggs
text: We recently became aware of Cara's Cafe and really wanted to try it. Cara's Cafe was previously Frankie's Deli and we had been there a few times and really enjoyed it. We got a glimpse of Cara's menu via Facebook and found quite a few entries we were anxious to try. We finally made it to Cara's yesterday (3 Jul 2020) for lunch.  We were greeted immediately upon entering and grabbed a paper menu to make our selections.  Making just 2 selections was tough, as everything sounded delicious.  For lunch, we opted on a Pesto Chicken Salad Sandwich on Croissant and the Mufalletta Sandwich on a French roll. Several counter pastries caught our eye as we were going over the menu so we added a piece of German Chocolate Cake, 2 Cannoli's, a frozen Peach Cobbler (for later consumption), and 2 Blueberry-Lemon cupcakes.  Cara's also offers frozen casseroles to take home and heat up, so we opted to grab a Jumbalaya with Conecuh Casserole for a 4th of July lunch.  After we received our sandwiches and our remaining order was bagged, we ventured over to the Alleyway in downtown Wetumpka for an outdoor table. Both sandwiches were EXCELLENT and the Italian Pasta Salad was DELICIOUS! We followed our sandwiches with the Cannoli's and cupcakes and they were just as DELICIOUS as everything else! While at the Wetumpka fireworks show last night, we gobbled up the German Chocolate Cake which was also DELICIOUS! We cannot wait to try the Jumbalaya Casserole today and Peach Cobbler.  We also had a great conversation with Bert and Katie while we were there.  They were so helpful and courteous! It goes without saying, we will be back to Cara's soon to try some other things...

I just ordered 2 more boxes for a friend and colleague, so he can have the Bake My Day experience.

name: michelle shadley
text: First time ordering from Bake My Day. Definitely a five-star experience all the way around. Got online to order something special for family and clients for Christmas that live out of the state. Saw that they were recognized nationally for having the best cookies to order online so I thought I'd give them a try. The ordering process was very easy. I was able to choose exactly what I wanted to send. The free priority shipping was a huge plus. I knew exactly when my order shipped out and exactly when they were delivered. The best part was that my clients and family thought the treats were absolutely delicious. Great customer service also.

resp.text: Hi Victoria, we are very sorry to hear you had a bad experience today. Our goal and intention is always to deliver the best product and experience for our customers. And we also have a policy of doing anything and everything we can to “make it right” whenever we learn of any issues or problems. That’s how we do business. It makes it very difficult for us to do our very best to satisfy our customers when we are not even given the chance or the courtesy of having time to make it right before a customer goes straight out to social media to post complaints and photos. It only causes harm to us as a small business. And as a business who holds quality and customer service at the highest level of importance this is very upsetting and disappointing. We also would like to clarify that we DO NOT put out “old” baked goods for sale. Thank you for your input. We will learn from it and strive to do better.

name: Morgan Roberts
text:
I sent cookies to a dental office and advised that they didn't work on fridays. So bake my day cookies said no problem. They sent the cookies priority mail monday and said they would get there wed. Well. They didnt arrive until Friday and were delivered to a po box, which is not the address I provided. So now the dental office will get old cookies on monday. I called bake my day spoke to Liz and they said oh well  . And they didnt do anything for me or the office receiving old cookies.  They didnt tske any responsibility and said its not their fault. Please be careful ordering online. Their website is deceiving. It says fresh cookies and 2 or 3 day delivery. All is a lie.

Look at the previous response from this company to the complaint before mine
It's also a lie. The did nothing to make my order right besides  blame someone else.

"And we also have a policy of doing anything and everything we can to “make it right” whenever we learn of any issues or problems. That’s how we do business. It makes it very difficult for us to do our very best to satisfy our customers when we are not even given the chance or the courtesy of having time to make it right before a customer goes straight out to social media to post complaints and photos. It only causes harm to us as a small business. And as a business who holds quality and customer service at the highest level of importance this is very upsetting and disappointing"

resp.text:
Hi Morgan,
We’re sorry that your cookies arrived late. They will still be delicious. As our shipping policy states, we send everything out to arrive in two days, which we did in your case. Unfortunately as with any merchant, we are at the mercy of the performance of USPS or UPS and have no influence on either. Both shipping services have a very high success right even in peak season and we watch this closely. It’s very disappointing for us too when they have delays which happened in your case.

As for delivery to a P.O. Box, I’m assuming that is a secure mailbox for the dental office that is used to protect their mail delivered outside of business hours. Again, that was for the USPS to decide. We shipped to the address you provided.

I explained this to you both times we spoke this week and apologized for the delay. We do our part to ship fresh cookies and purchase 2-day shipping, which is our responsibility. But the shipping services don’t offer guarantees on delivery and sometimes they let us all down. We’ve put extensive details about this on our website to make it very clear, and you checked a box in checkout agreeing to this policy. We did our best to get your cookies there on Wednesday, and the USPS obviously had some unusual performance issues this week.

Thank you for the feedback,
Liz
p.s. We have no bearing on when the Post Office or UPS delivers packages - no merchant does. You've made some pretty unfair statements about our bakery. When it's our fault, we don't hesitate to own it and fix it. While this case wasn't our fault, we've decided to refund your money.

name: Anne Martin
text:
Update: put a little heat in the pecan bar and WOW!! Worth a star!
Quaint little bakery and lunch spot. They have cookies, cakes, brownies and savory items for lunch or dinner, like soup & red beans. I just dropped in to check it out it was 4:30pm. They close at 5 and are not open on the weekends so it's been on my list for a while. It was a quick visit but I picked up a lemon bar and two pecan pie bars. They we're pretty good.

I'm a a huge lemon, anything, fan so I'm a tough critic. It was moist and the icing was full of flavor (I would guess it's confectioners sugar and milk with lemon flavoring)  the cake part was ok.
A little dense like a pound cake but it wasn't bad at all.

The pecan pie bar was a little square of pecan, what I would call soft ball stage, candy not really the consistency of pecan pie . The ratio pecan pie to crust was about 35/65.  I prefer more pie than crust, although the crust was done very well, flaky, beautiful color. But it didn't lack flavor,the gooey topping was very good , just not enough of it and I was really looking for a pecan pie on top of a crust.

I'll probably stop be there again to give it another try when I'm not in rush.

text: I am eating the chicken orzo soup right and it is fantastic!  The cookies are good, and a couple of my friends rave about the strawberry squares. I highly recommend Bake My Day for your lunch.

name: Robert Smith
text: Overall had a good experience at Bake My Day.  I stopped in for lunch and had the daily special which was a sloppy Joe sandwich, Cole slaw, Lays chips,  cookie and a drink.  Although it sounds like a lot of food it really isn't..  This is an order at the counter place with minimal seating.  4 small tables inside.  The counter terrorisperson was very friendly and pleasant (5 star).  The sloppy Joe was on a large bun and very good, tastef like a sloppy joe/bbq pork mixture, not sure though.  The Cole slaw was fantastic although a very small portion, it was in a small styrofoam side container and barely if even half full.  It was so good though I wanted .more.  The cookie was a small cookie but also very good.  The chips were typical Lays in a bag so they are what they are...  The sweet tea was very good and fresh.  Overall good food and a quick bite.  .More seating would be nice but it really isn't a restaurant so that can be overlooked.  I would have given it 5 stars but I felt the pricing ($10.25) a little high.  It would be better at around $9 for lunch and th⁰e slaw was so good it needs to be a fuller serving.  Overall I will go back to try the chicken enchilada and the taco soup as recommended by the friendly customers.  I would give it a 4.6 overall.

name: Y. Blue
text: This is not just a review, it's a WARNING.  If you expect a professional, courteous, or clean place to eat then this is not the place for you. I have frequented this place off and on for over 20 years and I have never seen its standards lower. After standing in front of the counter for 5 minutes while the employee socialized with one of his friends I was finally asked for my order only to be told that it would be a 10 minute wait. Okay, fine everyone likes warm fresh food so I consented. Then to my surprise the employee bags up a package of cinnamon buns and then gives them to his waiting friend for free as I'm standing there at the register. Where I come from that's called theft. Next, as other potential customers come by they are simply told that they are out of everything with the implication being the employees had no intention of preparing any more products. Then after another customer comes up who had obviously preordered, the manager is asked by the employee at the register to make change for a $20 which she goes in the back to retrieve only to return to kneading dough without any visible sign of having washed her hands and absent wearing gloves. Finally, after my 13 minute wait, the front counter employee tells me, "Oh, all I have is 1 order of cinnamon sticks" with the full knowledge that I had requested 3. When I asked who was in charge the employee initially stated that he was, then when I requested the contact info for a regional supervisor he retreated to the back office and returned with the previously aforementioned manager who then tells me that she is in charge. The two feigned politeness, but I'm certain it was only in an attempt to prevent me from contacting someone who is really in charge. My advice to the reader is DON'T WASTE YOUR MONEY or time at this establish. Or better yet, Don't Put The Health Of Yourself or Family At Risk by going here.
